title: easy yummy apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel the apples.
Take out the cores. Chop up the apple into small chunks.
Put the apples into a mixing bowl.
Stir the sugar into the apples.
Put the egg into the apples and add the oil.
Mix it all around.
Put in the nuts and raisins.
Using a sifter, pour flour into the bowl.
Put the baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and ginger into the sifter.
Sift these dry ingredients into the apple mix.
Mix it around.
With a little oil, grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake cake for 1 hour or until done by sticking a toothpick in the center to see if it comes out clean.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix flour, baking powder and 1 cup sugar with milk, stir well.
Pour into melted margarine. Cook fruit and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour fruit into batter.
Bake at 350 degrees until a knife inserted in it comes out clean.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: date roll
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Put in dates and cook until dates are melted.
Add nuts and cook for 1 or 2 minutes. Beat until creamy.
Roll in greased paper.
Wrap cold wet cloth around roll and let it cool and harden overnight.
Slice when chilled.

title: lemon love notes
directions: Blend 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar. Pat into 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 14 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Mix the lemon juice, eggs, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Place on crust.
Bake 25 minutes longer; cool.
Mix remaining powdered sugar, vanilla, 1 tablespoon butter and milk until smooth.
Spread on baked mixture.

title: fancy baked chicken
directions: Combine butter, cheese, garlic and salt.
Mix well.
Dip each piece of chicken in mixture, reserving remainder.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Place chicken in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining butter mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Stir powdered sugar into sour cream.
Fold cranberries and pineapple in and spoon into foil-lined saucepan or muffin cups with paper cups.
Freeze until firm and serve on lettuce with a pineapple ring.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator. Eat with crackers.

title: savory chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, and paprika together.
Shake chicken pieces in a tightly closed bag to coat evenly.
Heat oil in heavy skillet. Cook chicken over moderate heat until well browned on all sides.
Place chicken in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir soup and hot water into skillet drippings.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken. Spread sliced onion over all.
Cover dish.
Store in refrigerator 1 hour or longer.
About 1 hour and 15 minutes before dinner, bake covered casserole for 1 hour at 375°.
Uncover dish, sprinkle chicken with olives and bake for another 15 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Shape meat into balls and fry.
Remove and drain.
Empty jars of chilli sauce and jelly into crock-pot and add cooked meatballs. Stir well and cook on high for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat until ready to serve.
(Good as appetizer or over rice.)

title: chicken in honey-mustard sauce
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned; remove.
Pour off fat.
In same skillet combine soup, orange juice, mustard, honey and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 520 calories, 34 g protein, 69 g carbohydrate, 12 g fat, 70 mg cholesterol and 410 mg sodium.

title: cantaloupe salad
directions: Mix fruit in bowl.
Cook remaining ingredients over low heat, stirring until it thickens.
Cool.
Stir gently into fruit and chill.

title: no salt seasoning (low salt)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small jar with a shaker top.
Use for seasoning broiled fish, poultry, cooked vegetables, soups or stews.
Or, place it on the table to be used individually.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut meat into serving pieces, trimming fat and bone. On wooden board or wax paper, using meat mallet, pound mixture of flour, salt, pepper and meat. In large skillet over medium heat in hot oil, brown meat well on both sides. Arrange meat in 3-quart casserole dish. Place carrots and potatoes on top. Sprinkle with onion soup mix and cover with 3 1/2 cups water. Bake, covered, for 2 hours.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add vanilla, water and condensed milk.
Fold in mixture the whipping cream and add 1 cup coarsely ground Oreo cookies.
Put in loaf pan lined with foil and cover with foil and freeze for 6 hours.

title: holiday cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, combine sugar, orange peel, water, orange juice, oil and egg; mix well.
Add flour, baking soda and powder and salt; stir until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour in pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes; cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: german apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples, core and thinly slice.
In bowl, toss apple slices with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons ground cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, salt, eggs, oil, vanilla, orange juice, baking soda and baking powder.
With electric mixer, blend together on low speed for 1 minute.
Clean down side of bowl with rubber scraper.
Increase speed to medium and blend for 3 minutes.
You will have a very thick dough.
Fill prepared pan with alternating layer of batter and apples, making a total of 3 batter layers and 2 apple layers.
Start and finish with batter.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 10 minutes, then invert cake.
Remove pan.
Allow cake to cool completely on rack.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice vegetables lengthwise, then across in 1/4-inch slices. Steam zucchini and onion until a bit crisp and drain.
Mix sour cream and soup; add to zucchini.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing mix.
Layer the two, making top layer stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana torte
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread over the crust.
Slice four bananas over this.
Mix the instant pudding and the milk.
Pour this over the bananas.
Frost with the remaining Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator.

title: party dip
directions: With an electric mixer, gradually blend soup into cream cheese.
Beat just until smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve as dip for crackers or chips.
Makes about 2 1/3 cups dip.

title: vegetable soup(low cholesterol)
directions: Combine ingredients in a large pan.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Place sweet potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix hamburger with refried beans and garlic powder.
Layer in order:
noodles, hamburger mixture, salsa, sour cream, green onions, top with Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers again, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream oleo, brown sugar and egg.
Add baking soda, salt, flour, milk and vanilla.
Fold in rhubarb.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: texas hash
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Put into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add ground beef, tomato paste, water and corn; mix well.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage and chopped green pepper.
Blend together mayonnaise or salad dressing, vinegar, sugar, caraway seed and salt.
Toss mayonnaise mixture with vegetables.
Cover and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake by package directions.
Fill muffin cups lined with cupcake papers about
2/3 full of cake batter.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar, salt,
egg
and
then
add
the chocolate chips. Drop by rounded
teaspoonfuls
in
the
center of each cupcake. Bake at 350° for
15 to 20 minutes or until done, do not overbake. Cool on
wire rack.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir 1 cup of hot mixture into 3 beaten egg yolks.
Return mixture to saucepan. Bring to a gentle boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon peel.
Gradually stir in lemon juice.
Mix well.
Cool and spread on cake.
Yields 3 layer cake.

title: classic herbed chicken(serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine wheat germ and seasonings; set aside.
Combine water and egg white.
Dip chicken into egg white mixture and then into wheat germ mixture, coating chicken thoroughly.

title: super broccoli salad
directions: Soak raisins in warm water for 10 minutes and drain.
Combine broccoli, onion, raisins, and sunflower seeds.
Mix in the Miracle Whip and then pour over broccoli.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add bacon the next morning and allow to refrigerate another couple of hours.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, parsley and garlic.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add shrimp and simmer, uncovered, to desired thickness and until shrimp are cooked, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: holiday giblet gravy
directions: Saute flour and margarine until golden brown.
Add chopped vegetables.
Cook until vegetables become clear.
Add broth, soup, giblets and sliced eggs.
Cook slowly for 25 minutes.
Season to taste.
Serve over meat and dressing.

title: ground baloney spread
directions: Grind meat first, then add pimentos, pickles, onion and eggs. Mix very well with mayonnaise.

title: chicken slaw
directions: Mix salt, pepper,
vinegar
and
sugar.
Add to cabbage and toss lightly.
Toast sesame seed (watch carefully) and set aside. Add chicken,
carrot,
sesame
seed and almonds.
Last add noodles (uncooked);
crush in package.
Toss lightly.
Use packet in noodles to flavor rice later. Eat slaw while noodles are still crunchy.

title: delma's watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in dish.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Cover peas with water; soak overnight.
Brown sausage, stirring to crumble.
Add onion; cook until tender. Drain.
Drain peas.
In large pot, add peas with sausage; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add water if needed.
Great at New Years.

title: garnet punch
directions: Mix grape juice concentrate, apple juice concentrate, catawba grape juice and club soda in punch bowl.
Float scoops of sherbet on punch.
Serve immediately.
Makes 22 servings, about 1/2 cup each.
Good at Christmas.

title: ketchup
directions: Cook tomatoes, peppers and onions together.
Strain.
Cook in mixture of vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spice until thick. Water bath 10 minutes.

title: carrie's treats
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Let stand for 10 min. Form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: delicious cherry sauce
directions: Heat the pie filling with the pineapple juice and the ground cloves to boiling.
Serve hot with baked, boiled, or broiled ham.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Bake in tube pan and when cool, remove from pan and slice into two layers.
Scoop a tunnel from bottom layer.
Whip cream and add sugar and vanilla and whip until thick.
Drain juice from berries and save.
Fold berries in whipped cream and spoon this onto bottom layer of cake until full. Replace top layer and top with remaining mixture.
Dribble juice of berries over top and let run down sides.
Sides may also be frosted with plain whipped cream.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon to crisp; drain and crumble.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in bacon pieces.
May be served over lettuce or endive (either hot or cold).

title: steak, dressing and gravy
directions: Take a large cast-iron frying pan and 1 tablespoon oil and brown steak on medium heat.

title: layered salad
directions: Make and serve in a deep straight sided glass bowl.
Slice lettuce like cabbage and put in bowl until it is one-half full. Layer each item in order given.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Do not mix at any time.
Cut down through layers to serve.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Boil noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cook ground beef, onion, pepper, and celery.
Drain.
Warm soups and cheese until cheese melts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Grease sides of casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together in blender.
Cook the rest of ingredients hard for at least 2 1/2 hours and can it.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and shortening until fluffy. Beat in eggs and milk. In another bowl stir flour and baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Mix into sugar mixture; then add raisins and nuts. Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: golden cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, bouillon and seasonings.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended.
Add milk mixture to vegetables; cook until thick.
Add cheese; stir.

title: french chocolate drink
directions: Over low heat, melt chocolate with syrup and water.
Add vanilla.
Chill completely.
In cold bowl whip cream.
Gradually fold in chocolate that is cooled.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, put chocolate mixture into mugs, filling to half full.
Heat milk, but don't boil.
Pour over chocolate whipped cream; stir and serve.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until done.
Drain and then mix with beans, sugar, ketchup and seasonings.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: puerto rican potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, then peel and quarter them.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Top with green peppers, onions, pimentos, cubed cheese and margarine.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monster cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pepperoni calzones
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in 3 quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, oil, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turn, cover and let rise in warm place until almost doubled. Punch down and divide in half.
Put in 15 x 9-inch pan.
Spread sauce to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Top with pepperoni and cheese. Carefully fold over, pinching edges.
Place on greased cookie sheet; let stand 15 minutes.
Brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Slice diagonally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/3 dressing
on
bottom of greased casserole, then green beans (cooked
5 minutes previously), almonds and chicken and mushroom soup, then remainder of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot crab canape
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Remove from microwave and stir.
Microwave again for 2 minutes on High. Serve on small slices of rye bread.

title: daddy's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until it spins to threads. Add peanuts and cook until golden brown. Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients. Pour immediately onto a baking sheet lined with foil and spread thin. Let cool until firm. Break into pieces.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Press mixture into 14 x 4-inch dish.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: ocean isle crab cakes
directions: Combine eggs, salt, pepper, seasoning and mayonnaise.
Fold in crabmeat; add bread crumbs and shape into cakes.
Coat in bread crumbs and refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Saute in oil (vegetable) over low heat for 5 minutes per side or until delicately browned.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Saute onions, celery, and bell pepper in small amount of margarine or butter. Boil chicken and remove from the bone. Add Rotel tomatoes, soups, cheese and bouillon to onion mixture. Boil spaghetti in water where chicken was boiled; drain. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: men like it salad
directions: Mash cream cheese and pineapple, blending well.
Add nuts and celery.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; when cool, mix with cheese.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, lime juice, lime rind and egg yolks with electric mixer at medium speed until light.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and fold into lime mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Add cream of tartar and sugar to egg whites and beat until stiff enough to peak.
Pile lightly on filling and bake in slow oven (325°) for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before serving.

title: brandied fruit cake
directions: Combine Wesson oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs, then add dry ingredients (sifted together).
Add brandied fruit, nuts, vanilla and extra juice.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
If using a tube pan, bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar, flour and salt in a heavy saucepan. Combine milks and egg yolks; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove pudding mixture from heat; stir in vanilla.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello according to directions. Add pineapple and carrots. Let congeal.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine coffee with 1 1/2 quarts water.
Boil for 20 minutes. Strain through a lightly woven cloth.
Cool.
Add sugar and bring back to a boil and boil 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla and grain alcohol.
Serve with cream on ice.

title: working person lasagna
directions: Use lasagna pan and layer starting with noodles, meat, sauce and cottage cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: pepper cabbage slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and carrot in food chopper.
Add diced bell pepper.
Add 1 tsp. salt and cover for one hour.
In a sauce pan, heat the sugar, vinegar, and water until sugar is dissolved. Cool. Add cooled mixture, celery, and mustard seeds to the cabbage mix. Stir and enjoy.

title: yuletide drops
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Stir in sour cream.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in oats, pecans, dates, raisins and chopped cherries.
Drop from rounded teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: low-fat graham cracker crust
directions: Spray 9 to 10-inch pie pan with light vegetable oil 3 times. Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: low-fat beef stroganoff
directions: Toss meat in a plastic bag with 1 tablespoon flour.
Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add meat, stirring until meat loses most of pink color.
Stir in mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until meat is cooked and vegetables are tender-crisp.
With slotted spoon, remove meat and vegetables to platter.
Blend water and flour.
Add bouillon and add to pan.
Over medium-high heat, stir until mixture is smooth and thick and bouillon is dissolved. Reduce heat to medium-low.
Return meat and vegetables to sauce. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until heated through but not boiling.
Serve with noodles, rice or wild rice.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut sauerkraut strands shorter with scissors.
Stir in sugar, let stand 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, cover tightly. Chill at least 12 hours before serving.

title: d.j.'s delights
directions: Bring Karo syrup and brown sugar to a boil; add peanut butter and mix well.
Add nuts and Chex, mix and press into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
(A double recipe makes a cookie sheet pan size 9 x 14-inch.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add rest of ingredients and fold in whipped cream.

title: honey candy(kids can do)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Chill before serving.
Makes about 24 balls.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy-bottomed pan. Stir in the flour and blend over moderate heat until smooth. Continue to cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Add the chicken broth, continuing to stir as the sauce thickens. Bring to a boil; lower the heat and cook 2 minutes more. Pour in the cream and heat thoroughly.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil, and dry ingredients. Stir in apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in greased and floured 9x13 pan for 45-60 minutes at 350 degrees.
Top with whipped topping or frost with :

title: cabbage salad
directions: Pour boiling water over vegetables and let stand 1 hour. Drain well.
Mix other ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep 2 or 3 weeks.

title: chocolate-peanut butter topping
directions: Use equal amounts of each if larger amount is needed.
A little Karo syrup or milk can be used to thin topping.
Pour over ice cream.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll dough into 2 rectangles.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press onto bottom and 1/4-inch up sides of pan to form crust. Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, salad dressing and seasoning; mix well.
Spread over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place torn lettuce in a large glass bowl. Then layer on carrots, ham, peas, onions and cauliflower.

title: 7 day pickles
directions: First Day:
Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water; let set overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Put bread crumbs on top. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: best ever fried shrimp batter(for approximately 2 pounds of peeled shrimp)
directions: Mix all ingredients very well and add peeled shrimp to mixture.
Allow shrimp to stay in batter for as long as possible. When ready to fry, dredge each shrimp in flour and fry in deep, hot oil.
Serve hot.

title: homemade vegetable soup to can
directions: Mix together; cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: lemon-aniseed pound cake
directions: Position
rack	in
center of oven and preheat to 350°. Grease and
flour
1/2 x 12-inch loaf pan.
Using electric mixer, cream
butter
and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy. Beat
in
yolks
1 at a time.
Blend in peel, aniseed and vanilla.
Sift together
flour,
baking
powder
and
1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix into
batter alternately with milk.
Using electric mixer with clean
dry beaters, beat whites with pinch of salt and cream of tartar
in large bowl until stiff but not dry.
Fold half of whites
into
batter
to
loosen.
Fold	in remaining whites. Spoon half	of
batter
into
prepared pan. Sprinkle
evenly with espresso
powder.
Spoon
in
remaining batter.
Bake until golden brown and tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 1
1/2 hours.
Cook 20 minutes in pan. Invert onto rack and cool completely.
Chill overnight.
Bring to room temperature before slicing.

title: choc-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Drop tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: ham and eggs au gratin
directions: Mix butter and flour to paste.
Slowly add milk; stir and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese, mustard and Worcestershire.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add ham and eggs; heat through.
Serve over toast or corn muffins.

title: grant's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil fryer until meat falls off bone.
Remove meat from bone and return to broth.
Add Sweet Sue's chicken broth.
Heat to boiling and add tortillas.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Add more salt and pepper if desired.

title: pepperoni stuffed mushrooms
directions: Microwave butter, onion, green pepper and chopped stems from mushrooms until tender, about 3 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stuff mushrooms.
Place in a round dish and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until done.
Give dish 1/2 turn 2 times during cooking.

title: pig's feet
directions: Put all ingredients in large cooking pot and bring to a rolling boil.
Lower heat to slow boil for about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove feet and set in large bowl.
Strain liquid and pour over feet.
Refrigerate until solid, then remove fat from surface.
Serve with boiled potatoes.

title: harvest baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart baking dish, mix together B&M beans, catsup, vinegar, maple syrup, brown sugar, dry mustard and apples.
Arrange bacon slices over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of platter.
Pour chili sauce on top and spread.
Spread eggs, then shrimp and crab. Chill until ready to serve with Ritz or other crackers.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in half of the water. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover loosely.
Keep at room temperature for 24 hours.

title: chocolate fudge sheet cake
directions: Sift in large bowl sugar and flour.
Bring to boil oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Stir well while cooking.
Add to sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk
and baking soda together.
Add
2 eggs slightly beaten and vanilla.
Mix well and add to ingredients in large bowl.
Bake in sheet pan for 20 minutes @ 400 degrees or less.

title: creamy homemade ranch dressing
directions: Combine in a blender and mix well to incorporate all the ingredients.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Put apples in saucepan and heat.
Flavor and sweeten to taste with cinnamon and sugar.
While apples are heating, put 1 cup butter in ovenproof baking dish.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven temperature to 350°.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Shape into loaf in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Score top.
Preheat conventional oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes or microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes, turning dish after 6 minutes.
Top with remaining sauce.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Must set 12 hours in refrigerator before using.
Bake 15 minutes in 425° oven.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Add butter; let melt, then add corn and soup.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: cheesy hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until slightly tender.
Drain; set aside.
Brown ground meat and onions in skillet.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
In 1-quart casserole dish, spoon in 1/3 of meat mixture. Add cooked macaroni, then the remainder of meat.
Spread cheese soup over all (may be frozen, unbaked).
Cover casserole tightly and bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: nacho salad dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, seasoning and 1/2 package Cheddar cheese together. Spread on platter, top with taco sauce, lettuce, tomato and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, chili and diced chili peppers evenly in that order in a 14-inch round or rectangular Pyrex dish. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese is melted.
Serve with salsa chips.
Dip and eat.

title: caramel cocoa peanut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cereal in a plastic bag and crush, using a rolling pin.
Combine crushed cereal and butter; press mixture on bottom of a 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over cereal crust.

title: zippy appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients; spread on jelly roll sized pan (10 1/2 x 16 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm.
I often freeze them and reheat in oven or microwave.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Drop 2 tablespoons batter per pancake into hot, well-greased pan.
Fry over medium heat.
Turn once.
Both sides should be crisp and golden.
May be served with sour cream and/or applesauce or topped with grated cheese.

title: green chili meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, eggs, crackers and 1/2 cup ketchup with hands.
Put half of mixture in meat loaf pan.
Slice chilies lengthways.
Place on meat mixture in loaf pan.
Top with cheese slices.
Put remaining meat mixture in pan, top with another layer of cheese slices.
Lightly spread 1/4 cup ketchup over all.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add all vegetables; cook until tender. Cook rice.
In a casserole mix together the vegetables, rice, cheese and soups. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: lisa's lazy day gumbo
directions: Sprinkle K Paul's seasoning on chicken.
Combine celery, onion and green pepper.
Fry chicken.
Make a dark roux with 1/2 cup leftover oil from chicken and flour.
Add vegetables to roux and simmer.
Place stock in large iron pan; boil.
Add dark roux, fried chicken and raw blue crabs.
Simmer all day.
Remove chicken from bones and return to gumbo.
Add seasonings to taste.
Serve over white rice.
Excellent with hot French bread and ice cold beer.

title: brown sugar pecan rounds
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
Will flatten and spread.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until set (chewy-crisp).
Yields 3 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Cook ground meat and onion together.
Add tomatoes, paste and sugar. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cooked spaghetti together with butter and beaten eggs.
Form a crust. Spread with cottage cheese.
Top the cottage cheese mixture with ground meat mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broiled mushrooms
directions: Preheat broiler.
Wash and trim mushrooms.
Cut stems flush with bottom of mushroom.
Place on broiler pan, cap side down. Salt with celery salt.
Add dollop of sour cream to 1/2 of the mushrooms.
Put Cheddar cheese on rest of mushrooms.
Broil 2 or 3 minutes.

title: cheese - sausage balls
directions: Mix together until crumbly.
Form into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: party beans
directions: Cook bacon and saute onion in bacon grease.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well. Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool and top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be stiff.
Grease two or three small loaf pans and place batter in same.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bridal salad
directions: In small bowl, add jello, sugar and hot water.
Mix and cool 10 minutes.
In large bowl, beat cottage cheese for 2 minutes; add pineapple, pecans, Cool Whip, marshmallows and coconut.
Pour jello into mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 20 people.

title: pizza desert
directions: Combine cake mix plus 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons butter in large bowl.
Beat at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Blend remaining crumb mixture with egg. Press into greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Combine reserved crumb mixture, 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons butter, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spread crust with pie filling.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt the butter in top of a double boiler.
Add cornstarch and sugar.
Make a small paste.
Add the vinegar and water slowly, stirring constantly, until they start to boil.
Add the beets and cover double boiler until the beets and sauce become a rich red.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine cabbage, onions, noodles and water chestnuts.
Place sesame seed and almonds on a cookie sheet and brown slightly in oven, then add to salad.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Fill same jar with water.
Pour sugar and pickling spice in; stir mixture.
Put peaches into mixture.
Use large pan or pot; let boil for 20 minutes.
Use pint size jar.
Pour juice in jar with peaches.
Delicious with greens or beans.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture starts looking like play dough in spots (2 to 3 minutes), dump on a cookie sheet.
Let cool and knead well.
Keep in refrigerator in plastic bag or container. Lasts a long time.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Combine turkey with next 6 ingredients.
Form into meatballs; roll in flour.
Brown in a skillet with a small amount of vegetable oil or margarine.
Press the meatballs flat as they brown.
Place into small casserole (1 1/2 or 2 quart).
Cover with undiluted soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice and a vegetable.

title: honey 'n spice barbecued chicken
directions: Combine 57 Sauce and honey; set aside.
Grill or broil chicken pieces about 25 to 30 minutes, turning once.
Brush with reserved 57 Sauce mixture.
Grill an additional 10 minutes, turning and brushing with sauce.

title: broccoli noodle soup
directions: Heat
oil in large pot.
Add onion and saute for 3 minutes. Add water and bouillon cubes; heat to boiling until cubes dissolve.
Gradually add noodles and salt while mixture continues to boil.
Cook uncovered 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli and garlic.
Cook 4 minutes; add milk, cubed cheese and pepper.
Continue cooking until cheese melts.

title: overnight cinnamon french toast
directions: In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and vanilla until blended.	Place bread on a rimmed baking sheet and slowly pour the batter over.
Turn the bread until it is all coated with the batter.
Press a piece of waxed paper directly on the bread to cover it.
Refrigerate overnight.	Before serving, melt butter or margarine in skillet or on grill.
Fry bread over moderate heat until golden on both sides.
Do not crowd.
Serve with Cinnamon Syrup.

title: maryanne's cheesecake
directions: 1. Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
2. Sift & heat cocoa, margarine, and coke to boiling point
3. Pour over first mixture & stir well.
4. Beat together milk, eggs, soda, vanilla, and marshmellows.
5. Add to flour mix (Mixture thins with marshmellows on
top).
6. Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes in 10 x 13 pan.

title: chocolate crispies bars
directions: To melted chocolate, add butter, sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
While warm, cut in squares.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: specialty a la batts
directions: Bake according to directions (round pans).

title: jan's 24 hour green salad
directions: Mix shredded lettuce with all the vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise with Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic and sugar; cover vegetable mixture.
Cover dish and chill in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving. Grate the eggs over the top and sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: orange kiss-me cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan. Combine 1/2 cup orange juice thawed concentrate with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Beat slowly 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Drizzle remaining juice over warm cake.

title: crock-pot red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and place in crock-pot.
Cover with water; then chop onion and cut sausage.
Add sausage and smoked ham.
Fill crock-pot almost to top with bean mixture.
Add enough water to barely cover.
Cook on high, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Cook rice according to package directions.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet. Mix good in bag big bowl. Use juice, too. Mash chips in bowl or pan for crust. Put rest meat in next, then 1/2 cheese, then put rest of ingredients in on top. Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Steak should be 3/4 to 1-inch thick.
Wash meat, trim.
Fry fat for oil in a high dome electric skillet.
Cut meat into serving pieces 2 x 4-inch.
Prepare seasoned flour.
Pound seasoned flour into meat with mallet.
Dredge with seasoned flour, both sides. Fry meat.
Add shortening or margarine if needed.
Add 2 tablespoons seasoned flour to make a roux.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered 1 hour.
Check for sauce thickness. Add water if needed.
Check meat for tenderness.
Simmer until meat is tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine gelatin and sugar, dissolve in hot water.
Add lemon juice and reserved pineapple syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Turn into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to lukewarm milk.
Add melted shortening, well beaten eggs and flour.
Beat thoroughly to make smooth batter.
Cover; let stand overnight in cool place.
Stir well and bake on hot griddle.

title: peanut butter candies
directions: Put sugar in a bowl; add water, a little at a time (mixture should be thick).
Add vanilla.
Put a piece of wax paper on table. Sprinkle with flour, put 2 tablespoons of mixture on wax paper. Sprinkle with flour.
Roll mixture until flat, like a pancake. Spread with peanut butter.
Roll it, cut it in half.
Roll again until about 1-inch thickness, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Put on a plate in layers with wax paper between them and refrigerate until cold.

title: instant hot spice tea
directions: Combine lemonade, Tang, sugar, tea, spices and salt.
Makes 2 cus dry mix or enough for 6 quarts of tea.
For individual servings, place 3 well rounded teaspoons of mix in a cup and fill with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.

title: mammy's old fashioned freezer ice cream
directions: If you like fruit, use 1 cup of your choice.

title: crunchy cheese rounds
directions: Blend cheese and margarine.
Sift flour and spices into cheese mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Work with pastry blender or hands.
Pinch dough into small balls 1-inch in diameter.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and press down with palm of hand. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 11 dozen.

title: apple brownies
directions: Stir-mix until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients and ham cubes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey scaloppine gourmet
directions: Flatten turkey breasts, press into mixture of flour, cheese and seasonings.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet over medium heat, saute.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saut onions and celery in butter. Add seasonings, bread crumbs and broth. Add beaten eggs last. Cook in crock-pot on high 45 minutes. Reduce to low and cook 4 to 8 hours.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Arrange
chicken
in
a
9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Place a
slice
of cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Combine
the cream of chicken soup with the white
wine.
Spoon over each chicken breast.
Melt butter and add the crushed stuffing mix to it.
Sprinkle stuffing mixture over the
chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: super cheese ball
directions: In food processor, place all ingredients except for sharp cheese and blend well.
Gradually add the sharp grated cheese through the feed tube with machine running all the while, a little at a time, until all is included.
If mixture becomes too heavy for machine, add 2 to 3 tablespoons more mayo to thin.
Should be as smooth as velvet.
Enjoy!

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Combine with dry Italian seasoning mix.
Chop onion tops in tiny pieces; add to cheese mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Make into ball or log.
Roll in pecan pieces.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and drop by teaspoonful into hot grease.
Brown and serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large bowl mix bran and boiling water.
Cool.
Add eggs, buttermilk, oil and raisins.
Blend.
Stir together soda, salt, sugar and flour.
Stir into bran mixture.
Bake as needed at 425° for 20 minutes.
Cover the rest, place in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In saucepan, melt oleo; add celery and onions.
Saute and add soups and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sliced Velveeta to mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Add rice and mix well. Add broccoli (not cooked, just not frozen).
Add water chestnuts. Mix until creamy.
Put in large 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Makes about 16 to 20 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Layer bread, sausage and 3/4 cup of cheese into a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Mix milk, salt, eggs, mustard and rest of cheese.
Pour over layers.
Cover and place in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: mosaic bean souphouston, texas
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Measure out 2 c. gift packages.
If you can't find all the beans, substitute another variety.
To each package add a separately wrapped packet of:
1 1/4 tsp. salt, 1/2 tsp. pepper, 1 bay leaf, 1/4 tsp.
cumin and 1/4 tsp. ground cayenne.

title: bible times bread(like boy had with the fish jesus blessed)
directions: Turn oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add oil and water.
Stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Break dough in pieces and make into small loaves.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm with butter and honey.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, cocoa and melted oleo together.
Stir in coconut, pecans, milk and vanilla.
Pour ingredients into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This will make 3 small pies or 2 large ones.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. Add eggs, mayonnaise, onion and soup. Mix and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put grated cheese on top. Combine butter and herb stuffing and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: general lee bread
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and let stand in a bowl for 5 minutes.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and add 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water, oil, salt and sugar.
Gradually add the plain flour to mixture.
When you can no longer stir the dough with a spoon, turn onto a floured board.
Grease your hands and begin to knead for about 10 minutes or until you have a smooth, round and very elastic ball of dough.
Grease a large mixing bowl and place dough in the bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth and let stand in a warm place for about 1 1/2 hours.
Dough should double in bulk. Turn the dough onto floured board.
Grease loaf pans and your hands.
Divide the dough into 2 parts and place in loaf pans. Cover with damp cloth and put back in warm place for 1 hour or until dough has doubled in bulk.

title: "secret" hunan chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients (except oil) and marinate for at least 2 days, but 3 will be better.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes with a vegetable brush; dry with paper toweling. Rub skins all over with vegetable oil to keep them soft.
Place potatoes in a large shallow pan.
Bake in same slow oven (325°) with roast for 1 1/2 hours, or until potatoes are soft.
Remove from oven, but leave heat turned on.
Using pot holders to protect your fingers, make a slice lengthwise from top of potato and leave off.
Carefully scoop out the insides with a teaspoon.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Use empty soup can to measure the broth.
Cook chicken and take off bone.
Melt margarine and pour over dressing mix in a large bowl.
Add chicken broth and mix.
Pour into a well-greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
Put chicken on top of dressing.
Combine soups and pour over this.
Sprinkle some dry dressing on top.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Thaw broccoli at room temperature, then add mayonnaise, sour cream and soup mix in large container.
Chill about 2 hours and serve with Wheat Thins or your favorite crackers.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Brush bread slices on both sides with the melted butter.
Cut the bread into cubes and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Watch carefully after the first 10 minutes of baking because they will burn quickly.
Cool and use immediately or store in an airtight container.

title: good chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and liquids and mix together.
Stir in sour cream and chocolate chips.
Pour into a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.
Cake is better if stored 24 hours.
Cake will keep longer in the refrigerator

title: sausage and beans
directions: Brown sausage and chopped onion and drain.
Pour into slow cooker.
Add drained green, lima and yellow wax beans, then add kidney and pork and beans with liquid.
Add mustard, brown sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer until ready.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips over medium heat with Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Pour over prepared crust.
Top with nuts and remaining chocolate chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Unroll and flatten out 1 tube
of crescent rolls on the bottom of
an ungreased 9 x
13-inch
pan.
Pinch
all
seams together to form crust.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and syrup.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until filling is firm.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place croutons in a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Combine next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Pour egg mixture into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: german sweet rice
directions: Cook rice in water until tender.
Add sugar and milk and cook until thickened.
Add evaporated milk; stir through.
Add margarine, letting it melt over the top.
Sprinkle the top with cinnamon before serving hot.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Crush 1/2 pound O.T.C. crackers.
Chop hard-boiled eggs and add to crackers.
In a greased casserole, layer crackers, then a layer of oysters, lumps of butter, salt and pepper.
When all is layered, pour oyster broth over all and then cover all with milk. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook Minute rice with 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup Italian dressing.
Cook and drain English peas. Mix all ingredients together.

title: potato bake
directions: Allow the hash browns to defrost.
Mix soup, sour cream, butter, cheese and salt in a large bowl.
Add onion and potatoes and mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a small bowl, combine the crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter. Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Recipe may be prepared one day, then refrigerated and baked the next day.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Brown onion and water chestnuts slightly in hot bacon fat. Drain beans, saving 1/2 cup liquid.
Mix liquid with remaining ingredients and add to onion. Cook, stirring until mixture boils. Add beans and heat thoroughly. Serve garnished with crumbled bacon.

title: grandma's nut cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening; add eggs one at a time.
Slowly blend in milk.
Mix dry ingredients and add to batter.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour and 20 minutes in Bundt or angel food cake pan.
May be glazed with icing.

title: aunt selma's gingersnaps
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, eggs, molasses and vinegar together. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill overnight.
Form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Do not bake too close together.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (electric oven) or at 350° (for gas oven).
You may dip the tops in sugar (colored red or green for the holidays) before placing on baking sheet for added interest.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter in frypan; saute onion until tender.
Stir in flour; remove from heat.
Add milk.
Heat to boiling point.
Stir until thickened; fold in chicken, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and chill good.
Heat oil.
Beat egg with water.
Spread crumbs on wax paper.
Shape in patties; roll in crumbs, then egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Fry in oil; drain on paper towels.
Serve with ketchup.
Serves 4.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: grecian almond macaroons
directions: Remove eggs from refrigerator 2 hours ahead.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Beat in sifted sugar.
Fold in flour and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate bottom ice cream dessert
directions: Make crust of 13 graham crackers and 2 tablespoons oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, melt 2 squares of unsweetened chocolate and 1/4 cup butter.
Add evaporated milk and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cook together to a boil.
Boil for 1/2 minute.
Stir.
Cool.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla to chocolate mixture when cool.
Pour and spread chocolate over crust.
Top with ice cream (softened).
Put into freezer until hard.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, eggs, sugar, margarine, evaporated milk, coconut and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Bring stock, spices and vegetables to a boil in large pot. Add macaroni and simmer 10 minutes.
Add meat, heat thoroughly. Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper until done, drain.
Add to Ragu Sauce in Pan and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Cook pasta according to package directions and drain when done.
Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Layer ingredients in this order:
pasta, dotted spoonfuls of cottage cheese, shredded mozzarella cheese then meat sauce.
Note:
The more meat sauce use the soupier the lasagna will be.
Continue layering to a depth of approximately 1 - 1/2 inches to 2 inches. After the last layer of meat sauce, sprinkle parmesan cheese generously over the top of the casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes, on middle rack of oven.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to full boil. Remove immediately from heat.
Mix in peanut butter.
Add cereal.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips over hot water.
Spread over first layer.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cook over medium heat in a saucepan until it thickens, resembling a custard.
Use a hand beater at the beginning to thoroughly mix ingredients.
Pour filling into baked pie shell. Add meringue and brown in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Refrigerate for best results.

title: margarine expander
directions: Mix in blender or whip.
More butter, less fat.
Will separate with time, so don't mix too much ahead.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut shortening into this. Add corn, egg and milk mixture.
Mix well.
Fry in skillet, using small amount of oil.
Use 2 tablespoons butter per corn fritter.

title: peach parfait pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch pie shell.
Heat 1 1/4 cups water to boiling. Remove from heat.
Add one 3 ounce package of orange jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 pint of vanilla ice cream, cut into pieces to hot liquid.
Stir immediately until melted.
Blend in 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Chill until mixture is thickened, but not set, 25 to 35 minutes.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups sliced fresh peaches. Turn into cooled, baked pie shell.
Chill until firm, 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: carrot soup(california style)
directions: Fry onion in 2 tablespoons butter until of golden color and add it along with all the other ingredients to the chicken broth. Simmer one hour.
When finished cooking, put in blender in small batches and blend.
Return to pot and add one carton whipping cream (or use milk, if calorie conscious) and white pepper to taste.

title: gingerbread house cookies
directions: Mix the shortening and sugar.
Add spices and molasses.
Mix the soda and salt into flour; mix, alternating the flour and the water.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thick and cut out with gingerbread cutter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water rapidly (covered) until just tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Keep carrots warm while combining cornstarch and orange juice in small pan.
Blend until smooth.
Add butter and honey.
Stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Add orange rind.
Drain carrots.
Add glaze and mix well.

title: microwave corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave 10 minutes on High. Stir and microwave 5 more minutes until bubbly or you can melt cheese and butter first, then add other ingredients and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
(Good served cold as salad.)

title: steak in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place foil in baking dish.
Place steak in pan.
Cut up onion in chunks with carrots and potatoes. Place all over raw steak.
Mix mushroom and onion soup with 2 cups of water.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover with top foil.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: dudley's dip mexicanna
directions: Spread beans on serving platter or shallow dish.
Blend dressing and taco sauce.
Spread over beans.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb jello
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water until rhubarb is of sauce consistency.
Add dry jello.
Chill in refrigerator with Cool Whip and fresh strawberries on top.
When rhubarb is new and juicy, cut water to 3/4 to 1 cup.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 2 hours on high.

title: lemon barbecued chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 4 serving portions.
Marinate in barbecue mixture for several hours.
Broil, turning and brushing often with marinade, until done.
Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 3 g, fat 24 g, calories 372.
One serving = 4 meat low-fat exchange, 2 fat exchange.

title: golden corn and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except paprika.
Pour into a buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Mix and let set overnight in refrigerator.
This will keep for several days in a sealed container in the refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat mixture until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in loosely packed coarsely grated zucchini.
Add flour sifted with cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pans; then remove.
May be frozen for later use.
Wrap in foil to freeze.

title: rice-crisp cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, margarine and vanilla and mix until creamy.
Add egg and beat well.
Blend in sifted flour, then fold in cereal until just combined (do not overmix or beat).
Onto nonstick cookie sheet, drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls, forming 12 cookies and leaving a space of about 2 inches between each.
Using moistened tines of fork, flatten each cookie slightly.
Bake until cookies are golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Using a spatula, remove cookies to wire rack to cool.

title: hearty meat dip
directions: Brown meat together; add all ingredients except cheese. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Break cheese into large chunks and add to meat mixture.
Heat on low, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.

title: candy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple with juice, egg and vinegar in small pan.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Cool. Fold mixture into whipped topping. Add apples and peanuts.
Refrigerate.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients except cereal; set aside. In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add pumpkin, oil and cereal.
Mix well.
Slowly add dry ingredients, mixing until combined.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread in ungreased Bundt pan. Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Place in bottom of baking dish. Cook and mash potatoes with milk and butter, or make instant. Place potatoes on top of hamburger.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup together in a bowl.
Pour in pot. When it starts to boil, cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Beat egg white.
Gradually add syrup mixture to egg white.
Add vanilla.
Beat with a spoon until ready to drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or pour in a buttered dish.

title: greek oven brown potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch slices and put in a roasting pan. Add bouillon to cover potatoes; then add lemon juice and butter. Sprinkle black pepper over.
Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are brown and done.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients 1 minute at slow speed, then 5 minutes on high.
Mix dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan for 70 to 80 minutes.

title: favorite dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate before serving.
This recipe can easily be cut in half for a smaller portion.
Also, the shrimp is purely optional; it is a terrific dip with or without the shrimp. This is a great dip with crackers or vegetables.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Cook chicken, bone and cut into small pieces.
Mix other ingredients to make a sauce.
Place half of sauce on bottom of large baking dish.
Roll chicken pieces in unrolled rolls that have been divided.
Place on sauce in pan.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Mix in order.
Chill for about 4 hours or overnight.

title: peppered almonds
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Stir all ingredients in small baking pan to coat almonds. Arrange in single layer. Bake until coating is crisp and almonds are toasted, stirring occasionally, about 12 minutes. Cool. Sprinkle on salad.

title: chili bean corn bread dish
directions: Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: sunny day punch
directions: In punch bowl combine pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade concentrate,

and 4 cups cold water. Chill thoroughly. Just before serving add bottle of lemon lime carbonated beverage. You may garnish with orange slices and mint leaves if desired for color. Makes about 32 five oz. servings.

title: red cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage. Mix all other ingredients and add to chopped cabbage.
Let stand overnight.

title: broken glass candy
directions: *Do not use regular
extracts;
use oil flavorings such as cinnamon, wintergreen, spearmint
or
lime.
I use cinnamon oil and red food color, a big hit at Christmas.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If it seems too dry, add a little more milk.
Shape in a loaf and bake at 325° until done.

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with strawberries if desired.

title: cheesy shell lasagna
directions: In a nonstick skillet, cook the beef, onions and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in tomatoes, spaghetti sauce and mushrooms. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Cover with 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You can substitute tuna instead of chicken.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil jello and pineapple juice; let cool.
Mix cottage cheese, pineapple and pecans.
Sprinkle in marshmallows.
Set in refrigerator and thicken.
Add whipped whipping cream.
Pour into mold and let set.

title: canned salsa
directions: Wash, peel, core and chop tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a 6 to 8 quart pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; boil gently, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into hot sterilized jars; leaving 1/2-inch headspace at top.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars and adjust bands. Completely submerge in a water bath canner for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 pint jars of salsa.

title: fig jam with jello
directions: Bring all the ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Put into clean, hot jars and seal with wax.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend and pack into a 4-cup mold; chill at least 3 hours. Serve with crackers.
Can be frozen.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt stick of butter.
Add mixture of flour, sugar and milk.
Just pour it on top of melted butter. Lay fruit and fruit juices on top.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes at 400°.
Top will be golden brown.

title: crab dip
directions: In a double boiler, melt the cream cheese and butter.
Add the crabmeat and seasonings.
Serve in a chafing dish to keep warm. Good with dip-size corn chips, in pastry shells or crackers.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a large baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour on top of butter.
Pour peaches on top of mixture. Don't stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: spaghettini ala puttanesca(the whore's spaghetti)
directions: Heat olive oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
Add onion and chile and cook until onion is soft.
Add garlic, tomatoes, olives, capers and oregano.
Raise heat so this begins to boil gently.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened (20 minutes).

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; cook until softened. Stir in next 4 ingredients until well blended. Add tomatoes and broth; simmer 15 minutes. Stir in both peppers; simmer 10 minutes. Add squash and cook 10 minutes more. Add beans and peas, undrained, and simmer until heated through. Stir in cilantro.

title: pear bread
directions: Using wire whisk, beat eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and lemon together.
Add dry ingredients, mixing with wooden spoon.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Add pear pulp and mix well.
Bake 24 muffins for 22 to 25 minutes at 350°. Loaf pans will need to bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Happy eating!!

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling, spread evenly.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly
over cherry
layer. Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl; blend 1/2 minute on low.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in oblong or 35 to 40 minutes in layers.

title: garlic beans
directions: Mix ingredients together in casserole dish and bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Boil potatoes in water; drain. In large stock pan, add bacon (crumbled), potatoes, both cans of soup and milk. Cook over low heat for about 20 minutes. Add cheese slices, salt and pepper to taste. Add more milk if too thick.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Combine chicken broth, soy sauce and wine.
Cut beef into thin strips, about 1 inch long.
Cut on the diagonal.
Season meat with salt and pepper.
Cut broccoli into flowerets about 2 inches long and slice celery diagonally into 1/2-inch slices.
Chop onions. Preheat wok or skillet over high heat for 2 minutes.
Add oil, pouring around sides of wok or swirl around skillet.
Heat for 2 minutes.
Stir-fry meat and onions for 3 minutes.
Add broccoli, celery and mushrooms, stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Add bean sprouts.
Add chicken broth mixture.
Combine cornstarch and water and blend into meat and vegetables.
Bring to a boil, stirring for one minute.
Can be served over rice, if desired.
Can also be made with a turkey tenderloin cut similar to the beef.

title: apple nut dessert
directions: Mix sugar, sifted flour, baking powder, shortening, evaporated milk and vanilla with a fork until well blended.
Stir in chopped apples and nuts until well coated with batter.
Spread evenly in greased 9-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, softened butter and the 1/3 cup flour; sprinkle over apple mixture in pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until top is golden brown.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble all of cornbread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer beans, green pepper, onions, pickles and tomatoes.
Mix 1/2 cup pickle vinegar with mayonnaise and spread on top.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chiffon pie
directions: Put milk in freezer for 30 minutes.
Bring pineapple juice and Jell-O to a boil.
Let cool while beating milk.
Add together and pour over vanilla wafers after you have lined a pan with them.

title: mushroom risotto(may be used with pollo de peones del felipe)
directions: Peel and chop the onion fine.
Clean and slice the mushrooms. Saute the onion and mushrooms in the oil in a heavy saucepan until soft and golden brown.
Add the rice.
Saute for a few minutes, until coated.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Cover.
Cook over medium-low heat until rice is cooked (about 40 minutes).
Consult rice package for cooking time which varies.

title: double french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups dressing.

title: easy pizza
directions: Thank God for dirty dishes,

title: gooseberry pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except gooseberries.
Add enough flour to make batter stiffer than cake dough, add gooseberries. Put in greased 8 by 8 in. pan. Bake at 350° until done and golden brown. Serve warm with cream and sugar or whipped topping.

title: man-pleasin' meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk for 15 minutes.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Place in large oblong baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Combine rice with seasonings and amount of water specified on the package (omit butter).
Stir in remaining ingredients, including marinade from the artichokes.
Chicken breasts may be cooked in amy manner, then added to rice.

title: coconut ice cream balls
directions: Make ice cream balls in advance, using a scoop.
Roll in coconut.
Place on cookie sheet; place in freezer until ready to serve.
Looks beautiful in sherbet glasses.
Pour over ice cream balls.
For a more gourmet taste, use Kahlua instead of chocolate syrup.

title: cornell barbecue sauce(from ithaca journal)
directions: In blender, whip egg.
Then add oil, vinegar, salt, seasoning and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Marinate chicken overnight; also can use to baste as cooking.
Can be kept in a jar in refrigerator for weeks.

title: brown stew
directions: Thoroughly brown meat on all sides; add water, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion, bay leaves and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours; stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Continue cooking 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Thicken liquid for gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve in bowls with garlic spread French bread and a tossed salad and maybe fruit for dessert.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Mix well and serve in a glass fruit bowl.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Make night before serving.
Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese.
Place in flat rectangular dish; cover and place in refrigerator and let stand overnight.
Take out about an hour before baking.
Top with crushed potato chips and cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 or 40 minutes or until it bubbles.
Easy and good.
Serves 8 people.

title: pintos plus
directions: Bring beans to boil.
Stir in cooking sherry and soup mix, salt, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Reduce to simmer. Fry sausage, drain fat and add to beans.
Simmer 4 to 6 hours. Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water and blend into beans stirring until thickened.
Add sour cream.
Simmer until hot. Add cooking sherry to taste.
Cook beans until tender and serve.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into small pieces and boil in water until soft; drain off excess water and mash real well.
Add margarine while hot.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add to potatoes.
Mix well; add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into a Pyrex dish and bake until done.

title: magic pie
directions: Measure everything into a blender.
Turn on high speed and count to 10.
Pour into greased pie plate.
It will magically settle into layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab stuffed flounder
directions: Melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Stir in chicken broth and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add wine.
Combine 1/2 cup of the sauce with crabmeat and bread crumbs.
Spread on fillets, roll up and place seam down on a greased baking pan.
Dot with margarine and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat remaining sauce and pour over rolls. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: "page's" peanut butter cookie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in peanut butter, sugar and almond extract.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Makes 2 loaves. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: denise's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes or until done.

title: veggie bites
directions: Place crescent rolls on cookie sheet and roll flat.
Brush with beaten egg whites.
Bake at 375 degrees for 3 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
In mixing bowl, combine 2 cups sugar, vegetable oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Beat in juice and vanilla while alternately beating in flour mixture. Combine well.

title: beef and broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 30 minutes or until tests done.
Serve with a salad for a complete meal.

title: osgood pies(makes 2)
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Mix well and add vinegar and egg yolks.
Mix together flour, spices, nuts and raisins and add to first mixture, mixing well.
Fold this mixture carefully into beaten egg whites and pour into two unbakes pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until filling is browned.

title: apple valley cake
directions: Combine sugar,
oil, eggs and diced apples.
Set aside.
Sift together remaining ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Pour ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan and bake for one hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Place pineapple slices in a baking dish.
Place pork chops over pineapple.
Put one onion slice over each chop, 2 teaspoons of barbecue sauce over each onion and 1 tablespoon of brown sugar over each onion.

title: corn and crawfish soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and blend.
Saute onions in this until soft.
Add stock and cook until thick and smooth.
Stir in cream, crawfish tails, corn and seasonings.
Cook until tender. Adjust seasonings to taste.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 pints.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix eggs, oil, vanilla and pineapple.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and carrots. Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: carnival corn
directions: Combine sugar, molasses, water, vinegar and salt.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to light crack stage (270°).
Remove from heat; add butter and soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn and peanuts.
Toss well.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook ground beef until lightly browned.
Drain fat. Add onions and green pepper. Cook until onions are tender. Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat and pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Beat margarine with sugar replacement until creamy.
Add vanilla, water and flour, mixing well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese; add flour, salt, red pepper and paprika.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 4 rolls (1-inch in diameter).
Wrap each roll in foil.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Slice rolls 1/4-inch thick and place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 16 dozen.
Dough or wafers, after baking, may be frozen!

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and put in a greased loaf pan. Baste with brown sugar mixture last 1/2 hour of baking. Bake 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute salt pork or bacon slowly until done.
Remove from pan. Stir-fry onion in drippings until soft.
Add potatoes, water, clam juice and salt pork.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done. Add clams, milk, butter and salt and pepper.
Simmer to heat; do not boil.

title: pork chops dinner
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops. Lightly dust with flour. Fry chops in a 4-quart Dutch oven. Layer vegetables, then chops alternately to top. Add tomatoes and juice; top with parsley. Cook at low temperature until carrots are fork-tender. Serves 6 to 7 people.

title: potato, chicken, broccoli bake
directions: Cut chicken breasts into four pieces.
Sprinkle with pepper, dill and garlic.
Saute in skillet until brown.
Arrange in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes and onions and arrange over chicken.
Cut broccoli into bite size pieces and put over potatoes. Mix soup and milk and pour over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until potatoes are soft.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In a large Dutch oven or crock-pot, combine all ingredients and cook until vegetables are done.
Can be cooked on low in crock-pot all day.

title: mechelle's barbecue beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt and garlic powder.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Pour liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce over meat.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning once.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Pour barbecue sauce over beef and bake 30 more minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put milk, uncooked rice and margarine in top of a double boiler.
Cook for 1 hour.
Let cool for 2 hours.
Add rest of ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream pudding
directions: Cook milk, cornstarch, sugar, egg yolks and salt until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and butter until well blended.
I use this recipe for rice pudding (just add 3 cups cooked rice and 1 cup raisins) and also banana cream pie.
Easy and delicious!

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs to shortening.
Mix flavoring and pineapple to egg mixture.
Blend in dry ingredients and bake at 350° until golden brown but soft.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground chuck and onions; pour off fat.
Blend in pizza sauce, garlic salt and oregano.
Put mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella. In small bowl, mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour.
Pour over meat mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: do ahead fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fettucini with sausage
directions: Brown sausage, then drain grease.
Cut 3 peppers (long pieces), then add peppers, onion and garlic to the sausage and saute on low.
Boil fettucini, then drain.
In a large baking dish (greased), throw fettucini and stir around with fork.
Then add sausage ingredients; stir again.
Add half and half and cheese. Stir really well.
