Bake in oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine with 1/2 cup melted butter, salt, pepper and onions. Add cream of chicken soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend thoroughly and put in greased casserole, 9 x 13-inch.

title: fried catfish
directions: Wash fish thoroughly under cold running water.
Combine corn meal, salt and pepper.
Beat egg with milk.
Dip fish in the egg and milk mixture.
Roll each piece of fish in corn meal mixture to coat thoroughly.
Heat oil (2 to 3-inches) in deep fryer or Dutch oven to 375° or heat oil 1 1/2 to 2 inches in heavy skillet until hot.
Fry in deep fryer or skillet until golden brown on both sides, 5 to 8 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: homemade light biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to buttermilk.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add liquid; work lightly.
Roll and cut like any biscuit.
Let stand 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 400°; bake for 15 minutes.

title: sunshine fizz
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in electric blender container or food processor. Blend until smooth. Stir in "soda" drink of choice. Serve immediately. Yields 8 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain REAL well (very important). In 1 and 1/2 quart baking dish, melt 1/2 stick margarine and 1/2 lb. Velveeta cheese either in the microwave or over a pan of boiling water (homemade double boiler). Blend well. Pour over broccoli and mix. Melt 1/2 stick margarine or butter in a small frying pan. Coarsely crumble about 1/2 stack Ritz crackers. Fry in butter until well coated and hot. Pour over broccoli. Bake 20-30 minutes at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up; slice about 1/2-inch thick.
Serve with salsa.

title: salmonburgers
directions: Drain salmon; flake.
Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into 4 or 5 patties.
Pan-fry in small amount of vegetable oil until lightly browned on both sides.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.
Top with favorite condiments.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare instant rice by mixing in the water that has been brought to a boil.
Cover, remove from heat and allow to sit for 5 minutes.
You now have 2 cups rice to use in recipe!

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour.
Roll dough on floured board to 1/4-inch or 1/2-inch thick. Cut in small squares or diamond shapes.
Bake at 275° for about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
While hot, sprinkle with fine granulated sugar.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash according to package directions.
Drain well. Saute onions in margarine.
Stir well.
Add 3/4 of stuffing mixture to squash mixture.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes more.
Garnish with squash slice and celery leaves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pork chops with onions
directions: Trim chops.
Brown chops 5 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan.
Put onions in and brown.
Add water, rice, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place chops on top.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Then cook over low heat for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over noodles.

title: chilled chicken and vegetable salad
directions: For dressing, in a blender container, combine cottage cheese and catsup.
Cover and blend until smooth.
In a small bowl, stir together cottage cheese mixture, egg, onion, pickle relish and salt; set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat the oven to 375°F.
Spread the apple slices in an ungreased 8 in. pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake uncovered until the topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 min.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove bones.
Cook broccoli until tender.
In casserole dish, layer the chicken and broccoli. Mix soup and mayonnaise together and spread over chicken and broccoli.
Add salt and pepper.
Add grated cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: praline yams
directions: Arrange yams in shallow buttered dish.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with sugar and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until thick.
Add jello.
Add drained strawberries.
Mix and pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: chicken divan
directions: Pre-cook broccoli and chicken.
Blend soup, milk, sour cream, mayo, lemon juice and cheese.
Oil pan.
Lay out broccoli.
Cover with chicken pieces.
Pour sauce over top.
Pour bread crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: artichoke bread
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and sesame seed; cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned. Remove from heat.
Stir in artichoke hearts and next 3 ingredients.
Cover mixture and refrigerate, if desired, until ready to assemble.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center of each half, leaving a 1-inch shell; set shells aside. Crumble removed bread and stir into artichoke mixture.
Spoon evenly into shells and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Place on baking sheet, cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncover and bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: walnut loaf cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside. Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts; blend.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix water with chocolate and heat until melted. Cool.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Turn out onto serving plate.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles until just tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain and add margarine.
Let cool and then add eggs, already beaten.
Add jam, raisins and cinnamon.
Pour into greased, lasagna sized baking pan and bake at 350 F for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: coconut cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Grease two 8-inch or 9-inch round cake pans (flour pans).
Sift flour before measuring.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, flavoring, milk and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini pie(mock coconut custard pie)
directions: Peel zucchini and remove seeds.
Cut in pieces.
Cook in water until soft.
Drain and mash 1 1/2 Cups.

title: johnny marzetti(serves 6)
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Cook ground beef, drain and add onions.
Mix noodles, ground beef, soup and spaghetti sauce together.
Add cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut up elephant into bite size pieces.
(It will take about 2 months)
Place in a large pan; cover all the pieces with gravy. Cook on a kerosene stove at 350° for about 4 weeks.

title: bill's milk chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and set aside the flour and sugar.
Mix in a pan to melt the oleo, cocoa, water and shortening.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture and mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *May substitute 1 can cream of celery soup in place of mushroom soup if desired.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Mix in salt.
Mix in sugar (slow and thoroughly), working in vanilla.
Mix up on the side the chocolate chips, together with walnut meats and fold into the mixture.
Drop by spoonful onto brown paper on a cookie sheet. (No grease.)
And while so doing, get your oven up to 400°.
Slide the Forgotten Kisses into the 400° oven; close oven and turn heat off.
Don't open oven until morning.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon and drain on paper towels, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute apples, shallots and ginger in hot drippings 5 minutes or until tender. Remove from heat; stir in sage. Stir together apple mixture, bacon and cheese in bowl.

title: italian tuna salad toss
directions: Place greens on serving platter.
Arrange artichokes, tuna, beans and tomatoes over greens.
Top with dressing.
Serves 6.

title: world's easiest peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together.
Drop spoonful of dough onto cookie sheet until filled.
Press each cookie with fork to make crisscross pattern.
Sprinkle sugar on tops of each cookie, then bake for 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
It's easy to cut recipe in half or double, triple, etc.

title: country club muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon color. Mix remaining ingredients in order.
Fill greased miniature muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. These freeze well.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Place chicken into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Cover each piece of chicken with a slice of cheese.
Spread dressing over cheese.
Pour chicken soup over all.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Warm pumpkin and add butter, sugar and salt.
Add well beaten eggs, milk and flavor.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers and drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all together and put in greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut almond carrot roll
directions: Mix
flour,
baking
powder,
salt
and cinnamon.
Beat sugar and
oil
at
medium
speed of electric mixer until well mixed. Stir in flour mixture.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in carrots, nuts, raisins and 2/3 cup	of coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pan or 6 cup
ring mold.
Bake
at
350° for 35 minutes, or until done.
Cool	in pan
minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling.
Frost with
cream
cheese
frosting
and cover with remaining coconut.

title: macaroni-tuna casserole
directions: Combine macaroni, water and salt; cook until slightly under done (5 to 7 minutes).
Drain and use later.
Set oven to 350°. Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onions and pepper until tender. Remove from heat; stir in soup, tuna, mustard, milk, salad dressing and cooked macaroni.
Turn into buttered casserole; top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: berry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine egg, milk and melted shortening.
Add this to dry ingredients and drained fruit.
Stir until just mixed.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chili - wendy's
directions: Brown meat, add soup:

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Roll into walnut size balls (50 to 60). Place, not touching, on greased jelly roll pan.
Freeze until firm.
Pack in plastic bags and bake as many as needed on ungreased pan in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Great to make ahead and have on hand when company shows up!
Three balls contain 9 gr fat and 133 calories.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: On bottom of casserole,
layer bread, cheese and sausage.
Beat eggs; add 2 1/4 cups milk and mustard.
Pour this over the top.
Next, mix
1/2 cup milk with soup; pour on top. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, until set.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown venison and onion together; drain excess grease.
Add enchilada sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix together cottage cheese, eggs and parsley.
Shred cheeses.
Layer tostadas (these are prepackaged and cooked, like taco shells), meat mixture, cottage cheese and Monterey Jack cheese.
Keep layering as you would lasagna.
Put the Cheddar cheese on top.
Sprinkle crushed tortilla chips around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 1/2 hour.

title: easy cinnamon twists
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll each biscuit into a 9 inch rope. Pinch ends together to form a circle. Dip biscuit circles in melted butter, then in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Twist each biscuit to form figure 8. Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake in 425° oven 8 to 10 minutes. Serve warm. Makes 10 twists.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together except potato chips and put in shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at least 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and milk until smooth. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then flour and milk alternately.
Start out with cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup potato chips in slow cooker. Top with remaining chips. Cover. Cook on low 4 to 5 hours.

title: quick creamy chicken
directions: Set stove at medium-high
setting.
Spray frying pan with Pam (or oil).
Saute sliced onion and add chicken, cut up in 1-inch pieces.
Heat until browned.
Reduce heat to low and add mushrooms (undrained) and soup.
Add salt, pepper and parsley to taste and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cheesy vidalia onion casserole
directions: In a medium glass bowl, microwave onions, covered in plastic wrap, on High 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Stir once, then add salt, basil and pepper.

title: butternut grahams
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good, by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic detraction and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Prepare batter for cake mix according to package directions. Turn into a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan which has been greased and floured.
Cover batter with rhubarb.
Sprinkle rhubarb with granulated sugar.
Pour whipping cream over ingredients in pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly.
(Cream and rhubarb sink to bottom, forming a lush custard layer.)
Makes 15 to 18 servings.
Store any leftovers in refrigerator.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Fry bacon slowly until crisp.
Crumble and reserve.
Line pie pan with pie crust and cover it with mixed bacon and ham.
Combine eggs, milk, cheese and seasoning.
Pour over bacon and ham mixture.
Cover with top crust and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes until crust browns.

title: chocolate chip cookies(yields 100 cookies)
directions: Blend flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and brown sugar for 2 minutes in mixer on low speed.
Add shortening, butter or margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix for 1 minute on medium speed. Add chocolate chips and peanut granules (optional).
Blend for 30 seconds on medium speed.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain, if necessary.
Add undiluted soup, spaghetti, cooked, mixed vegetables and mushrooms.
Bake in a 12 x 9-inch baking dish for about 30 minutes, or until bubbly. Sprinkle cheese on top after removing casserole from oven.

title: lemon glazed chicken
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in shallow pan.
Mix lemonade and soy sauce together and pour over chicken.
Bake on top rack of preheated 400° oven, turning once and basting occasionally.
Bake for 40 minutes or until the chicken is brown and fork-tender.

title: chocolate pie(microwave recipe)
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cocoa together; add enough milk to stir.
Add egg yolks, beat well with electric mixer.
Add rest of milk.
Cook 5 minutes on high power in microwave.
Stir melted butter and vanilla.
Cook additional 5 minutes and stir. Microwave watts may vary cooking time.
You want filling to be thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: ham and swiss pocket
directions: You can toast pita bread, microwave or put in oven at 450° for about 5 minutes.
I like mine toasted so it is crunchy.
Take cooked pita bread and stuff with ham and cheese.
Put tomatoes and Ranch dressing on top.
Put in microwave or oven just until cheese is melted.

title: punch
directions: Stir sugar into warm water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and freeze.
Take out to thaw to mush about 2 hours before use and add 1 part Sprite (cold) to 2 parts punch.

title: chicken-potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in deep saucepan. Add onion and cook until onion is tender, but not brown. Add chicken broth, chicken and potatoes. Cover and cook for 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add milk.
Mash 1 or 2 pieces of potatoes with spoon. Stir well.
Yields 3 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add most of the water.
Cook until it boils, stirring all the time. Add lemon juice and butter or margarine.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar, 1 at a time, until the egg whites stand in peaks, stiff and glossy.
Pile on top of filling in a baked pie shell.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon curry deviled eggs
directions: Blend in 8 oz. cream cheese, 1 chopped bell pepper, 1 small chopped onion and 1 jar of chopped pimiento. Add pimiento juice if necessary.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Boil water.
Saute onion, celery, pepper and add to boiling water.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add carrots, potato, garlic and spices.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cauliflower, broccoli, zucchini, spinach, corn and tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli, then mix all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch dish (sprayed with Pam).
It's easier if you microwave the Cheez Whiz first to soften.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add ginger ale and cream cheese. Stir until the cheese is dissolved. (You can use an electric mixer to speed up the process.) Refrigerate for approximately 20 minutes. Add the drained pineapple and pecans. Stir well and refrigerate.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
In a measuring cup, add egg and vinegar. Beat well.
Fill measuring cup up to 2/3 mark; add liquid mixture to flour mixture.
Ready to roll out (I chill mine in refrigerator a couple of hours).

title: lemon pie
directions: Set cream cheese out until room temperature.
Whip cream cheese until smooth, then add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix until smooth. Then fold in lemon juice.
Pour into family size graham cracker shells and chill.
Then add pie filling.
Chill.

title: easy dill pickles(mrs. fox 6185)
directions: Boil together.
After this boils, pour over the cucumbers and seal.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Trim edges off bread and cut into 4 strips each.
Melt the margarine. Add the sugar. Stir in the flour, vanilla and egg. Pour pie filling into square Pyrex dish.
Place bread strips on top of this.
Pour mixture on top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or topping.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Heat milk in saucepan over medium heat.
Mix cocoa, sugar and flour.
Slowly add to milk and stir.
Add salt.
Stir until like gravy.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut into chunks.
Combine with celery, eggs, lemon juice, drained and sliced water chestnuts, undiluted soup and mayonnaise.
Turn into casserole and sprinkle with bread or corn flakes and cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: savory beans
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water in saucepan.
Add beans; heat to boiling.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until tender. Season with pepper.
Serves 6 (25 calories per serving).

title: egg salad supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on toasted bread.

title: cranberry-apple relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add apples; simmer 5 to 7 minutes more or until slightly thickened.
Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate up to 4 weeks or freeze.

title: green salad with great dressing
directions: For Dressing:
Whisk or use blender or Cuisinart to mix the mustard, vinegar, shallot, sugar and salt.
Add oil slowly, mixing constantly, until thick and creamy.
(You can reduce the amount of oil and substitute water or plain yogurt for approximately 1/4 cup of the oil.)

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine onion and butter in a 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole.
Cover and cook on 90 (Saute) for 3 minutes, or until onion is transparent.
Add 1/4 cup water and stir in remaining ingredients except cocktail wieners.
Cover and cook on High for 2 1/2 minutes, or until sauce is bubbly.
Stir in cocktail wieners. Cover and cook on High for 4 minutes, or until wieners are hot. Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.
Serve warm; use toothpicks to spear individual wieners.

title: country cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, toss to coat well.
Cover and chill. Serves 8.

title: slush
directions: Bring the sugar and water to a boil.
Mix in remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream.
Store in refrigerator 24 hours or more.
Stir once or twice.
Bake cake.
Make 3 thin layers.
Spread coconut mixture on cake layers.
Finish by spreading coconut mixture on top and sides of cake.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 2 beaten eggs and 1/2 cup bread crumbs, and refrigerate for 1 hour or longer.
Heat oven to 400°. Shape the mixture into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls in 2 beaten eggs. Roll in 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Serve hot with mustard.

title: fruit filling
directions: Cover apples with water.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain.
While apples are hot, add remaining ingredients.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute' first 3 ingredients and put in casserole dish. Add rice, water, and soup. Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Add coconut, pecans and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread preserves over dough, crumble remaining dough over preserves. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan, cut into bars.
Yields 36 bars.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
I put them in muffin tins, then in plastic bags.

title: pineapple mallow pie
directions: Heat marshmallows, pineapple and lemon juice in saucepan (or double boiler) just until marshmallows are melted.
Stir constantly.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in the whipped cream. Put into pie shell and chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: blueberry cream pie(makes two pies)
directions: Crust:
Mix first three ingredients together with your hands and press into pie pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all well. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown at 400°.

title: quick ginger chicken
directions: Mix water, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and ginger together until smooth and set aside.

title: meat potato pie
directions: Mix ground beef, 1/2 cup soup, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasoning.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Top with prepared potatoes.
Pour remaining soup over potatoes.
Top with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: mrs. sam hissman's date candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and pinch of salt until it forms a hard ball.
Add dates and cook until it still forms a hard ball. Remove from fire; beat until real creamy.
Add coconut and nuts. Turn on a dampened cloth.
Shape and cut in nice size pieces.
Let dry.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine butter, water, cocoa and oil in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over mixture of sifted flour, sugar, salt and soda. Mix. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 11 x 16 x 1-inch.	Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and ice immediately with icing.

title: lime punch
directions: Combine sugar, drink mix and hot water; stir until dissolved. Cool.
In punch bowl, blend sugar syrup, juice and soda.
Spoon in sherbet.
Makes 22 cups.

title: caramel cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Gradually add sugar, creaming it until light and fluffy.
Add unbeaten eggs and beat well.
Alternately add milk and flour.
Begin and end with flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add flavoring.
Bake in layers in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding and cool a little.
Stir in one dry chocolate cake mix until well blended.
Pour in pan, then drop a few chocolate chips on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Flatten and brown chicken breasts in butter for 5 to 6 minutes. Take chicken out and add next 3 ingredients.
Put in mushrooms and cook; then add the wine.
Serve and garnish with parsley.

title: pork and noodles
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown sausage, then add onions and celery. Cook for ten minutes.
Add noodles, peas, tomato soup and water, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 45 minutes in oven at 350°.
Good with cole slaw.

title: aunt edna wilson's white feather cake
directions: Cream the shortening; add the sugar gradually.
Mix and sift the dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water.
Lastly fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Bake in layers in moderate hot oven (375°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Heat in double boiler or crock-pot all ingredients.
You can use sharp cheese and add a few drops Tabasco hot sauce if you can't find jalapeno cheese.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir together graham cracker crumbs.
Add peanut butter and melted margarine.
Roll into balls.

title: becky's gingerbread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening and add molasses, ginger, cinnamon, ground cloves, salt, flour and beaten eggs.
Mix this and set aside.
Add baking soda to boiling water.
Stir into other mixtrure (it will be thin).
Add raisins (optional).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until center springs back when touched.
Top with powdered sugar or whipped cream.
Good warm.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Flour chicken and turn in butter so both sides are wet.
Put in oven at 400°, uncovered for 15 minutes on one side, then take out and turn over and cook 15 more minutes on the other side.
While chicken is cooking for the first 30 minutes, mix your cheese, milk and soup together.
After chicken has cooked for first 30 minutes, take out; pour mixture over chicken and cover with tinfoil.
Cook 30 more minutes.
Can serve over rice.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: In a large, heavy pot, fry rice in oil, but do not brown.
Add onion, jalapeno peppers, broth, oleo, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cheese that has been cut into small pieces; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: kathy's cranberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars.
Stir in milk, orange juice and egg.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto greased baking sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Microwave peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows.
Microwave 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir until blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies and put in buttered pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut and enjoy!

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and strawberries.
Mix in sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in flour.
Bake in greased loaf pans (2 large or 4 small pans) for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken; saute mushrooms.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mushrooms and pimento.
Stir in chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry and salt.
Cover bottom of large baking dish with 1/2 crushed chips.
Fill with chicken salad and top with remaining 1/2 of crushed chips and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold bread pudding
directions: Add all ingredients in large bowl. Mix well with a beater. Pour into bread pan over the biscuits. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Allow time to cool, then serve in milk.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve the large package of jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Mix in bananas, strawberries (still frozen) and pineapple with liquid.
Chill until firm in an 11 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch glass baking dish.
(Size can vary.)
Spread with sour cream and chill 1 1/2 hours.
When firm, spread with 1 small package of jello that has been mixed with 1 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water. Spoon on carefully; chill until set.

title: coffee bar cookies
directions: Cream shortening or margarine and sugar together; beat in egg until light.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add half of hot coffee to creamed mixture, then dry ingredients and finally remaining coffee; stir until well blended after each addition. Fold in raisins and nuts.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 14 x 1/2-inch jelly
roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. When cool, spread with frosting made by combining
1 tablespoon butter and 1 cup confectioners sugar with enough cold coffee to moisten.
Cut into 3/4 x 2-inch bars.

title: homemade orange sherbet
directions: Put both ingredients in your home ice cream freezer.
Process until sherbet consistency. Crushed pineapple can be added.

title: pecan crisp
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour and vanilla. Spread batter evenly on cookie sheets.
Beat egg whites and spread over batter.
Sprinkle nuts on egg whites and press in.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until very light brown.
Cut in squares while hot.

title: baked corn dish
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into a deep 8 x 10-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cup of cheese over the top of the corn mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Better yet if refrigerated overnight, then set out until room temperature and baked.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Heat cranberry sauce, lemon juice, soy sauce and butter until melted.
Salt and pepper.
Lay chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake 15 minutes.
(Reduce baking time with skinless, boneless chicken.)
Good served with rice.

title: cake mix cookies - chocolate chip(great for kids to make!)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Stir well.
Add in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons to ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on pans, then remove to wire rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: buttercrunch(like crunch 'n munch)
directions: Combine butter, syrup and sugar in 1-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir occasionally until mixture boils.
Reduce heat slightly and continue cooking to stage that you can lift up spoonful and it is stiff when poured out of spoon.
Candy thermometer would be 260°. Pour over popcorn mixture and nuts and mix well.
If it is not hard enough
or crisp enough, place on a butter-greased cookie sheet; spread evenly and bake in 350° oven for about 5 to 6 minutes.
Store in tin container.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook celery, onions and bell pepper in 1 pint of chicken broth until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add more tomato soup or 1 cup canned tomatoes, if desired.
Top with cheese.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Place all in large container; mix well.
Use 1/3 c. mix per 1 c. hot water.

title: glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour over cake in pan while hot.
The cake may be cut in squares and served from the pan.
It may be kept in the refrigerator several days.
If using Martha White plain flour, increase baking soda to 1 1/4 teaspoons.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: thanksgiving mincemeat cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture well after each addition.

title: streusel-filled coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is fine like cornmeal.
Blend in well beaten egg mixed with milk, then blend in vanilla and beat just enough to mix well.
Pour half the mixture into a well-greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with half the streusel mixture.
Add rest of batter and sprinkle over top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: 1-minute fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for vanilla, peanut butter and salt.
Bring other ingredients to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and salt; beat with a mixer until smooth and glossy, about 5 minutes.
It will be thick. Pour into buttered dish or pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix margarine, egg and sour cream.
Add to flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Use loaf pan lined with aluminum foil for easy removal.

title: milky way cookies
directions: Melt all ingredients together over a low heat.
Stir well, then press into a shallow tin.
Allow to cool and set, then cut into pieces.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage with diced onion.
Drain.
Pour in saucepan.
Add Ro-Tel.
Bring to boil.
Cut up Velveeta and add to saucepan.
Cook on very low heat.
Great with chips or crackers.

title: 7 layer spinach salad
directions: Layer each ingredient in order.
Top with cubes of Swiss cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, then toss.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Brush brisket with hickory smoke on both sides.
Rub well with the 3 salts.
Marinate overnight.
Cover tightly in refrigerator. Bake, covered, at 250° for 3 hours.
Pour off half the juice and turn and bake 1 hour longer.
Pour barbecue sauce over and bake 1 hour longer.
Let cool and slice thinly.
Put in shallow baking dish covered with foil and freeze.
Reheat to serve.
This is so good to prepare and put into as many servings as you need for company later and freeze.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Put ingredients in heavy pan.
On medium heat, bring to a boil.
Boil to a firm soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until it loses its glossy appearance.

title: ranch potato cheddar casserole
directions: Toss together potatoes and mixture of Ranch dressing, sour cream, bacon bits and parsley plus 1/2 cup cheese.
Add melted margarine to corn flakes and the remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Cut oranges in small pieces.
Add sugar. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
In morning, add walnuts, grapes and crushed pineapple.
Add Jell-O with boiling water.
Mix all together.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Roll mixture in 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Take out 3 to 4 hours ahead.
When soft, stir in 2 large ginger ale.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Stir in water. Divide into jars. Add a few drops of food coloring to each. Store covered.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Take shrimp out of jar; keep sauce separate.
Soften cream cheese; add sauce.
Beat until smooth.
Add chopped shrimp, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.

title: duchess meat loaf
directions: Stir soup mix into water in a 2 cup measuring cup.
Use 1/2 cup and blend into ground meat.
Shape meat into a big "O" in skillet.
Cut into 6 wedges but leave in a circle.
Pour remaining soup mixture over and cover.
Cook on medium heat for 25 minutes. Spoon taters into skillet in globs and
drizzle juice over the taters.
Good!

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs and then remaining ingredients.
Pour into two (9-inch) aluminum foil pie plates and bake for about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: yellow squash dressing
directions: Stir all together the ingredients.
Boil ingredients for 5 minutes; turn into casserole.
Bake at 425° until consistency of dressing.

title: ham and cheese cakes(delicias de queijo e fiambre)
directions: Grease 15 to 18 muffin cups.
Work the flour, butter and salt with a little water until you have a manageable dough.
Roll out the pastry on lightly floured surface, about 1/8-inch thick. Divide the dough and line prepared muffin cups.
Add grated cheese and ham to each cup.
Beat the milk and eggs together.
Pour over cheese-ham mixture.
Bake in a moderately hot 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and margarine until well mixed, then add all other ingredients.
Form into ball shape.
Roll in nuts until ball is covered.
Chill until firm.

title: tropical smoothie
directions: Combine 1/2 of the first 4 ingredients in electric blender. Process until frothy.
Pour into stemmed glasses and garnish each with a whole strawberry.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: sausage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put rectangles of dough.
Press 1/2-inch up sides of pan and seal perforations. Layer cheese and sausage in pan.
Mix eggs, milk and seasoning. Pour over cheese and sausage.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted into pie comes out clean.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: zesty mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Steam until very soft.
Mash with potato masher or use electric mixer on low speed.
Add margarine and spices.
Gradually add in sour cream until creamy (usually about 4 ounces).
Serves 6.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch. Add the cold water. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until well mixed.
Divide the mixture into 4 or 5 portions and add a few drops of different food coloring to each.
If you add a pinch of detergent to each portion, it will be easier to clean up your finger paints after the children play with them.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.

title: hot bouillon
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart pot, combine bouillon, vegetable juice, bay leaf and oregano. Bring to a boil and simmer gently for 25 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add lemon juice and season with salt and pepper just before serving. Serve hot.
Sprinkle with parsley for garnish.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Peel pears, core and grind.
Grind all other fruit with peeling on. Place all ingredients in heavy cooker and cook until tender. Seal in clean containers.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream peanut oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat 10 minutes.
Add flour, milk and flavoring.
Mix well.
Turn into 4 prepared layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: leche flan
directions: Mix egg yolks, evaporated milk and condensed milk together on leche flan pan.
On separate cooking pan, heat sugar until it melts and then add to mixture in leche flan pan.
Cook in a steamer for about 1 hour.

title: salade mimosa
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic.
Shake vigorously in jar.
Arrange greens in a bowl.
Add dressing and toss well.
Sprinkle with chopped eggs.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Dredge meat in seasoned flour and brown well in drippings. Add water; cover pan and simmer for an hour.
Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Add vinegar, soy sauce and juice drained from pineapple.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and clear.
Pour sauce over meat.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Heat through.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat egg, buttermilk and oil.
Gradually mix together until moist and lumpy.
Cook over medium heat.

title: cranberry cooler("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Combine cranberry juice, lemon concentrate and water.
Just before serving, add carbonated beverage and
ice cubes.

title: cherry chewbilees
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Chop
nuts.

title: beef roast
directions: Butter bottom and 1/2 way up sides of pan.
Sprinkle onion soup in bottom of pan.
Lay roast on top of soup.
Put potatoes and carrots around roast.
Mix soups and 1 1/2 to 2 soup cans of water.
Pour on top of roast.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: overnight salad vegetable
directions: Shred lettuce into a large, flat glass baking dish. Press down firmly. Mix peas and onions, diced celery, pimento and green pepper and sprinkle over lettuce. Cover with mayonnaise and sugar mixture. Crumble bacon over top of mayonnaise. Add grated cheese, more green pepper and pimento for color. Seal tightly with plastic wrap and let set overnight.

title: best ever breakfast pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given. Fold in egg whites.

title: layered salad
directions: Use an 8 x 13-inch glass loaf pan.
Shred lettuce in bottom of pan.
Add green peppers, onion, celery, frozen peas and Bac*Os.

title: beef salami
directions: Mix well divide in half make two rolls wrap in wax paper.
Let stand in fridge. 24 hours.
Unwrap and cook on rack for 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: curry cajun spiced chicken
directions: In a 3-quart rectangular baking dish, combine honey, water, prepared mustard, butter, Cajun seasoning, curry powder, lemon juice and garlic.

title: pudding cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa together. Add milk, shortening and vanilla. Mix only until smooth. Put in greased shallow baking pan. Mix brown sugar and cocoa. Sprinkle over batter. Pour 1 1/2 c. boiling water over cake. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 egg in a bowl, mixing well.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: anise balls
directions: Sift
together
flour,
soda, cream of tartar and salt. Cream oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Add flour
mixture
and
anise
seed.
Mix
until well blended. Chill
for a couple hours for easier handling.
Roll into balls about 1 inch and bake on lightly greased pan 10 to 12 minutes at 350°, or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: gerry's sloppy joes casserole
directions: In frypan, cook meat and onion until done.
Drain off grease. While meat is browning, cook macaroni.
Combine meat, macaroni, chicken soup and corn.
Stir together until mixed.
Put in casserole dish.
On top, put bread crumbs, and a chopped slice of butter over crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until bread is brown.

title: deep dish chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water; batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes clean.
Frost with Fudge Icing.

title: pizza sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger and let cool. Add rest of ingredients. Put in refrigerator. When ready to serve spread mix on halved hamburger buns and bake at 425 degrees for about 10 minutes. Makes about 16-20 halves.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add fruit with juice.
Pour half mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: boxty(ash wednesday supper)
directions: Grate raw potato into a bowl.
Turn out onto a cloth and wring, catching liquid.
This will separate into a clear fluid with starch at the bottom.
Pour off the fluid and scrape out the starch.
Mix with grated and mashed potatoes.
Sieve the dry ingredients and mix in along with the melted butter.
Add a little milk if necessary to make a pliable dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Divide into 4 parts and form large flat cakes. Mark each into quarters, but do not cut through and bake on griddle.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a baking dish lined with crust made from crumbled corn bread; press down with melted butter. Crumble more corn bread over the top with melted butter over it. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix lemon juice and sugar with Eagle Brand milk.
Make layers as follows:
bananas, Eagle Brand milk mixture, pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut, pecans and cherries.
Do not mix.
Make the night before you eat.

title: old fashioned slush
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Let stand 5 minutes. Remove tea bags; squeeze gently.
Add sugar, stirring until it dissolves.
Stir in 6 cups water and next 2 ingredients.
Cover and freeze 8 hours.
(Can be frozen in small containers.)
To serve, spoon 1/2 cup bourbon mixture into a glass and add 1/2 cup carbonated beverage.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped bacon and onions in a skillet. Drain off excess fat and pour into a 9-inch square baking dish. Add ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and beans (drained).
Stir ingredients until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes. Makes six to ten servings.

title: oyster bisque
directions: In heavy saucepan, saute onion, celery and paprika in butter until transparent.
Bring oysters to a boil in the chicken broth. Pour liquid into sauteed mixture.
Add milk mixed with flour and heat until thickened; simmer slowly 5 minutes.
Add oysters and correct seasoning.
Improves with standing and may be refrigerated for 2 to 3 days.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup and melted butter. Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a moderate oven about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: burnt sugar candy
directions: Boil the first 2 ingredients until the soft ball stage. During the time this is boiling, burn 1 cup of sugar.
Put the burnt sugar into the boiling mixture and continue boiling until well done.
Beat until it begins to stiffen.
Add nut meats.
Pour onto a buttered plate.
Top with halves of nut meats.
Cool and cut in 2-inch squares.

title: easy zucchini bread #4
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix for 4 minutes.
Pour into pans and bake for 50 to 55 minutes until done.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder, spices and sugar. Cream shortening, add flour and soup alternately with nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle with flour before adding.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 60 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in undrained blueberries and pineapple.
Spoon into a dish and chill until set.

title: della's chicken-okra gumbo
directions: Smother okra in small amount of oil; set aside.
Make roux by mixing flour and oil together and browning slowly.
Add okra; add all other ingredients. Cook until chicken is tender (about 1 hour). Remove chicken.
Debone and replace chicken into gumbo.
Season to taste.

title: spinach dip
directions: Remove all water from spinach.
(I press the spinach between paper towels.)
Drain water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Serve with crackers or vegetable sticks.

title: southern pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet on medium high heat.
Put rice, green pepper, onions, salt, pepper and paprika in the bottom of a 1-quart casserole dish.
Place browned pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Pour tomatoes and bouillon water over pork chops.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add egg yolks, flour, vanilla, pineapple (with juice), coconut and sweet potatoes. Beat well. Beat egg whites from icing and add to batter last.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar and stir until blended. Add vanilla and pecans.
Form into small balls and dip into melted chocolate chips.
Cool on waxed paper to harden.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet. Will stay light brown in color. Makes several dozen normal size cookies.

title: tasty hamburger patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture into 6 patties, each about 1-inch thick.
Place patties on grill about 4 inches from medium coals.
Grill until desired doneness, 7 to 8 minutes on each side for medium.

title: crawfish or shrimp stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out "meat" of each potato half.
Mix with shredded cheese and bacon bits; set aside.
Saute the shrimp or crawfish in margarine with onion and bell pepper.
Mix in Ro-Tel and add to potato mixture.
If mixture is too stiff, add a little milk.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with mixer.
Add sugar.
Mix in eggs one at a time and beat well as you go.
Alternate milk and flour after it is sifted with baking powder 2 or 3 times.
Add flavoring.
Bake in 2 pans for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: simmering chicken strawberry kabobs
directions: In a shallow glass bowl combine lemon juice, juice from pineapple can, salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix together. Add cubed chicken and marinate for 1 hour in the refrigerator. Preheat grill to medium heat.
In a small bowl combine the melted butter or margarine, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, brown sugar and nutmeg. Lightly oil grate.
Using metal or soaked wooden skewers arrange chicken, pineapple chunks and strawberries on each stick (approximately 4 to 6 pieces of each item per skewer).
Brush kabobs with butter or margarine mixture place on grill and cook, turning on all sides, until chicken is cooked through and strawberries are sizzling, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt the butter.
Add to powdered sugar and stir well.
Roll into balls.
Place on pan and put in freezer about 25 minutes.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Cook in crock-pot 2 hours on high.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Add shortening, sugar, butter and mashed potatoes to yeast cake and water.
Let stand for 2 hours in a warm room.
Add 1 cup cold water, salt and flour and knead.
Put in bowl and let rise double in bulk; knead again.
Make rolls and store remainder in refrigerator in covered container.
Bake at 375° for 10 or more minutes.

title: sausage and egg brunch
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 11 x 7 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crispy oven baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into melted margarine.
Coat all pieces in mixture of Rice Krispies and sugar.
Place pieces on cookies sheet or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan lined with foil.
Bake uncovered at 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg with onion, stirring often to finely crumble. When cooked, drain grease and discard.
Add to hamburg the remainder of the ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes and serve. Makes 1 dozen sandwiches.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray glass dish with Pam.
Laye chicken breasts.
Place slice of Swiss cheese on top of each.
Mix together wine and soups and pour over chicken.
Cook Stove Top for 8 servings and place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: yesterday cake
directions: Melt the margarine; mix in the egg, sugar, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add the pecans and mix again.
Line a dish with the vanilla wafers and pour mixture over the vanilla wafers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon spread
directions: In a mixing bowl combine cream cheese, onion, lemon juice, horseradish and mustard.
Stir in salmon and mix well.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla until smooth. Spread over bottom of pie shell. Sprinkle pecans over this. Beat remaining eggs until frothy. Add corn syrup, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1 tsp. vanilla. Beat until blended. Pour this over pecans. Bake in 375° oven until knife inserted half way between the the center and edge comes out clean, about 40 minutes. Place on wire rack to cool.

title: mock turkey salad
directions: Mix all together.
Makes a delicious sandwich spread.

title: melt in your mouth chicken
directions: Cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Add chicken to chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: sesame stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl.
Add sugar and mix.
In a small bowl, combine soy sauce, sesame oil and sesame seed.
Pour over chicken.
Add onions.
Mix, cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Dissolve chocolate over hot water; set aside to cool.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time; beat until smooth.
Add chocolate and mint flavoring.
Pour into a baked pie shell and bake until done; cool.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: g & f bundt cake
directions: Add cake mix to eggs and sour cream.
Mix.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, add sugar, flour, potato chips, and vanilla; mix. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done.

title: microwaved seasoned potatoes
directions: Peel and dice into 1/2 inch cubes or smaller as many potatoes as you want to cook.
Wash the potatoes thoroughly and place them in a large microwaveable dish.
Excess water is ok with the potatoes.
If desired, chop your favorite onion and add to potatoes.
Scoop 2-3 large tablespoons of margarine into the potatoes and season everything with as much Tony Chachere's seasoning as you like.
The more you use, the spicier (hot!) the potatoes will be.
Stir it all up in the bowl and microwave on high for 5 minutes.

After the first 5 minutes are up, stir the potatoes to distribute the melted margarine and seasoning, and continue doing this in 5 minute increments until potatoes are cooked to your desired doneness, usually 15-20 minutes.
If cooked long enough, the potatoes will brown and crisp on the edges.
Serve with ketchup!

title: caramel corn
directions: Keep corn hot; bring other ingredients to boil and boil 5 minutes.
After boiling, remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon soda. Pour over hot popcorn and toss gently.
Oven bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: "vickie's" cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs, then flour until smooth.
Then add chocolate chips and nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a lightly greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Let cool, then slice into squares.

title: blue cheese sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with grilled beef and vegetables.

title: my mom's own pumpkin pie recipe
directions: Into large bow blend pumpkin, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour mixture into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake approximately 35 minutes more.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar with shortening.
Stir in eggs.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to shortening mixture; mix well.
Drop by level tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt butter in pan; use square cake pan to bake in.
Combine other ingredients well and pour in pan.
Bake at 400° until well done.
Top will begin to brown and bread will be springy.

title: irish baked lamb stew
directions: Slice half of potatoes very thin and layer them on the bottom of Dutch oven or casserole.
Slice onions 1/2-inch thick and layer 1/2 of onions over potatoes.
Arrange lamb cubes and bacon over onion and potatoes.
Sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper.
Add remaining onions and remainder of potatoes (left whole).
Pour in Lamb Stock.
Sprinkle with more salt and pepper.
Add bay leaf. Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast popeyes(children's favorite)
directions: Brush bread slices with melted butter or oil.
Cut hole in center of bread with cookie cutter or drinking glass (about 2-inches in diameter).
Place bread, buttered side down, on griddle or skillet.
Put one egg, removed from shell, in center of each slice of bread.
Brush top with butter.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes at medium heat; turn and cook until egg is done.
Place cut-out bread circles on griddle to make toast.

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: Combine all three cheese together.

title: seven layer green salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in 9 x 13 inch dish. Top with pepper, celery, red onion and peas.
Mix mayonnaise sugar and cheese together.
Spread on top of salad. Top with broken bacon pieces. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12-15.

title: southern squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Save 1 cup of flour to roll out in.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Deep fry in hot grease for about 2 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: oriental beef-rice casserole
directions: Brown beef, celery and onion.
Drain fat.
Mix in vegetables. Dissolve beef bouillon in hot water.
Mix with soup and soy sauce. Add to beef mixture. Stir in rice.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Place meat in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on full power for 3 to 5 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Drain.
Stir the tomato sauce, onion, garlic salt, basil and oregano into meat.
Cook on full power for 4 to 6 minutes until boiling.
Stir.
Set aside.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix together all ingredients and freeze.
Mixture will be slushy.
Place desired amount in serving glass or pitcher and fill with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In bowl, add and mix all ingredients, except mushrooms and cheese.
Put 1/2 of mixture in loaf pan.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Top with remaining mixture.
Form into loaf.
Bake 30 minutes, draining off excess fat.

title: thrifty tuna casserole
directions: Empty soup into a small bowl.
Add milk and mix.
Add tuna, crushed potato chips and peas.
Stir well.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tom wopat's beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Add meat; shake meat to coat.
Melt margarine in a large pan.
Brown meat.
Add beef broth.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Cover and cook for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until tender.
Add peas; cook until heated through. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Fills a punch bowl.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook to 300°, hard crack stage.
Stir often.
Stir in soda and vanilla. Spread on greased cookie sheet.

title: laurine's praline patties
directions: Combine sugars, syrup and milk; cook to a soft ball stage in cold water or 234° on candy thermometer.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add vanilla; beat by hand about 2 minutes.
Add pecans; beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto buttered foil or cookie sheet.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown beef.
Cut bacon in small pieces.
Saute with onions. Put in crock-pot and add all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low setting for 4 to 6 hours.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Wash rice in a sieve under running water.
To cook the rice, use 3 cups water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 cup wild rice.
Bring to a slow rolling boil and boil until the rice is flaky and tender when tested, approximately 30 minutes.
Drain, then steam dry over low heat to make it fluffy.
Set aside.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Combine eggs, bananas, vanilla, nuts and Raisin Bran.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir oil into cereal mixture.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda and add to cereal mixture.
Stir until well moistened.
Spoon into loaf pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until done.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 3 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with wax paper.

title: shrimp jubilee
directions: Remove shell and the vein on back of the shrimp.
Put in large frypan
on
medium heat with melted margarine and garlic powder. Cook
shrimp
just until it has turned pink and curled into ball.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from bone; cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups chicken broth, adding onion.
Cook until rice is done.
Add other ingredients.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with grated cheese 10 minutes before done.
Makes 1 large casserole or 2 small ones.
Can be frozen ahead or made day before.

title: the 6's ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Put in ice cream freezer container.
Finish filling with milk, whole or skim.
Freeze.
This makes a wonderful refreshing ice cream.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: fudge kisses
directions: Melt white chocolate; add oil.
Drizzle over cooled kisses.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Defrost strawberries and puree in blender.
Mix with lemonade (do not add water to lemonade).
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add 3 quarts cold 7-Up.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Butter one loaf pan.
Mix sugar and cocoa together in a microwave-safe bowl.
Top with margarine (cut into pieces) and milk.
Do not mix.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Remove from microwave and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla and stir until mixed.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Cut and serve.

title: apple muffins
directions: Cut shortening in dry ingredients.
Mix egg, milk and apple; add all at once to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes* or until golden brown.
Remove immediately, roll in 1/2 cup melted butter, then in mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Serve warm.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Preparation:
Mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream, taco seasoning and mayonnaise.

title: peaches 'n' creme
directions: Drain peach syrup into a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and stir in gelatin until dissolved. Let cool, but do not refrigerate. Stir in cottage cheese. Whip whipping cream (do not substitute). Fold in with peach slices. Pour into serving bowl and refrigerate.

title: sour cream onion dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: pepper relish
directions: Mince onion and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients to pan.
Simmer on low until all is soft.

title: shari's artichoke dip
directions: Use blender for artichoke hearts, then combine all the ingredients.
Place in a Corning Ware dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden at 350°.
Use large, round crackers for dipping.

title: red jambalaya
directions: Prepare Basic Creole Sauce according to recipe.
How much you need depends on how many you are going to feed.
For one gallon, you need approximately 2 pounds smoked sausage (sliced thin), the meat from 1 medium fryer (boil and pull meat) and 1 1/2 pounds (70 to 90) peeled and deveined shrimp.
Cook 2 pounds rice.
Freeze what's left.

title: mrs. lloyd's carrot salad
directions: Stir first 7 ingredients together.
Pour over prepared vegetables.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6 persons.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9x13 pan and add the rest of the ingredients in order. Place in 350 oven and bake for 25 minutes. Cut in squares when cool.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: In a large bowl, mix brown sugar, butter, syrup and soda. Cook 4 minutes, stir every 1 minute.
Pour syrup over popped corn and stir.
May add nuts.
Cook on high 1 1/2 minutes; one minute and stir, 45 seconds and stir, 30 seconds and stir.
Pour out on cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add other ingredients. Refrigerate until gelatin sets.

title: confetti rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon to a paper towel. Use 1/3 c. of the drippings. Add rice, carrots, celery and peas to the drippings. Cook until heated through, about 5 - 7 minutes. Stir in bacon. Serve with soy sauce if desired.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries and bring to boil. Pour over jello and add cherries, pineapple, cream cheese, nuts and Coke.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: asparagus shepherd's pie
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Meanwhile, brown beef in skillet; add onions and garlic.
Pour in soup and pepper.
Put in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Cook asparagus in water until crisp-tender, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Drain and place over beef mixture.
Drain potatoes; mash with milk, margarine and salt. Spread on top of asparagus.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain pineapple.
Chop the can of whole cranberries.
Blend or stir all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Cut into serving squares. Serve on lettuce leaf or alone.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Put into an 8 to 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar together. Set aside.
Combine milk and pudding; beat until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add creamed mixture.
Serve in a 9 x 13-inch pan, bowl or plastic flowerpot.
Layer cookies, 1/2 of mixture, cookies, other 1/2 of mixture and a final layer of cookies on top.
Chill. If using a plastic flowerpot, stick artificial flowers for fun.

title: cheese rings
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine together.
Add flour, salt and pepper and stir well.
Put in cookie press and press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add milk; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in oil.
Coat wieners with batter.
Cook in deep, hot oil until brown.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt margarine and shortening; stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla flavoring.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Put flour mixture in bag or on a plate.
Roll or shake steak until completely covered in flour mixture.
In crockpot place onion slices and the meat on top of onions.
Top with carrots and celery and cover with tomato sauce.
Cover and cook in crockpot low 8 to 10 hours or high 5 to 6 hours.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Fluff the softened cream cheese with an electric mixer.
Beat in the horseradish.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: barbecue-teriyaki sauce
directions: Cut chicken, spareribs, beef, shrimp or fish into bite-size pieces.
Soak for 1 hour in thoroughly mixed teriyaki sauce. Broil over charcoal or in broiler until well cooked.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and cut up broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Add in raisins and chopped onion.

title: cold dough cookies
directions: Mix flour and margarine.
Then add cream cheese, mixing thoroughly.
Divide dough into three balls and chill 1/2 hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup soup.
Shape into about 20 small balls.
Place balls into skillet.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 40 minutes.

title: viscotti(italian cookies)
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
and
make
a well in the center. Beat eggs, Crisco and vanilla; pour into the dry ingredients. Knead this mixture until the dough is well blended, as if for bread dough.
Shape cookies in twists and circles.

title: microwave chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces of white chocolate in a 2-quart dish for 2 minutes.
Stir and continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes until smooth when stirred every 30 seconds.
Remove and stir in marshmallows, cereal and nuts.
Pour in greased 12-inch pizza pan. Top with cherries.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Microwave remaining white chocolate and oil for 1 minute.
Stir and continue to microwave until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut and chill until firm.
Store at room temperature.
Cut into small wedges.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil.
Add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Cook, covered, in oven at 350° for at least 2 hours, until tender, or on top of stove, covered.
Simmer until tender.
When finished, cool.
Mix in the sour cream.
Serve over wide noodles.

title: garlic pot roast
directions: Cut 3 of garlic cloves into slivers and put into meat.
Brown meat on all sides in oil and chop onion and rest of garlic. Brown onion and garlic.

title: curried fruit
directions: Place fruit in buttered casserole.
Mix together the butter, brown sugar and curry.
Pour over the fruit and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: happy family stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, stir soup mix, water and ginger.
In a large skillet, heat 1 teaspoon corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove.
Heat remaining corn oil. Add beef half at a time.
Stir-fry 2 minutes or until lightly brown.
Return beef and broccoli to skillet.
Stir in soup mixture.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil and boil 1 minute. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: cheese roll
directions: Shred pimento and sharp cheese.
Mix in garlic salt, pepper, Tabasco and Worcestershire.
Add mayonnaise.
Add cut cream cheese and blend with hands.
Shape and roll in paprika.

title: ham loaf superb
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Shape mixture into loaf, 8 x 4 x 3-inches, in ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until done, 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Remove from oven; let stand a few minutes, transfer ham loaf to ovenproof platter.
Make slits about 1/3 of the way through loaf at 1-inch intervals; place a cheese triangle long side down in each.
Place loaf in oven until cheese is slightly melted, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: rumaki
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Drain crab meat.
Mix all ingredients with electric mixer. Bake at 350° until hot. Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce in saucepan; add margarine, sugar and raisins. Remove from heat and cool in saucepan.
Add salt, flour, soda and spices.
Add chopped nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange one layer of potatoes in bottom of deep baking dish, then layer of onion rings, sprinkled with flour, pepper and salt. Repeat until potatoes and onions are used.
Cut a stick of butter in 6 pieces.
Crush the bacon.
Sprinkle bacon and chopped green peppers on top of potatoes and onions.
Add enough milk to cover the mixture.
Dot the top with chunks of butter.
Bake approximately 1 hour in 350° oven or until tender.
Serves approximately 10 to 12.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with bacon strips.
Sprinkle rice. Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup with water and pour evenly over chicken.
Cover and cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Cook macaroni to al dente, according to directions on package and drain.	Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add onion and green peppers and cook with ground beef until soft.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat 2 jars of spaghetti sauce.
Place water in one of the spaghetti sauce cans, rinsing it and then the other one.
Add to sauce.
Remove from heat and add cooked macaroni and ground beef mixture.

title: nancy's syrian bread
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients.
Mix together milk and butter. Make sure this mixture is good and warm but not too hot as to kill the yeast.
Add yeast.
Mix together.
Pour warmed liquid mixture into flour mixture.
Stir well and add eggs.
Mix together well. Knead together well (about 7 to 8 minutes).
Let mixture rise in bowl for 2 hours.
Roll out and cut into symmetrical strips. Place in greased pan.
Cover with a damp cloth for 30 minutes. Pat down to 1/2-inch high.
Bake at 250° until bottoms turn brown. Place under broiler to brown tops.
Watch closely as to not burn.

title: raspberry layered parfait
directions: Mix cornstarch, 5 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Gradually add cold milk; stir until thoroughly blended.
Add scalded milk and cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add mace and almond extract, mixing well.
Cool.
Combine raspberries and remaining 4 tablespoons sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and salt in heavy kettle until mixture spins a thread. Add peanuts. Boil slowly until mixture is very yellow, almost brown and smells like roasting peanuts. Take off stove and add butter, vanilla and soda. Stir until butter melts. Pour onto 2 greased cookie sheets. When cold, break into pieces. More soda makes a fluffy brittle.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Yields 6 servings.

title: xtra good fudge
directions: In a large kettle boil sugar and milk for 8 minutes.
Mix in other ingredients until melted.
Spread in large buttered pan. Cool and cut in pieces.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll stew beef in flour mixture and brown.
Drain.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Add onion, tomato soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes; then add potatoes and carrots.
Bake 45 minutes longer.

title: cheesy hot bean dip
directions: In a medium skillet, cook celery, onion and minced garlic in oil over medium heat until celery and onion are tender, but not brown.
Stir in the refried beans, taco sauce, green chili peppers and chili powder.
Bring the mixture to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Gradually add small amounts of the shredded cheese to the refried beans, stirring occasionally, over low heat until the cheese is melted.
Transfer the hot cheese-bean mixture to a fondue pot or chafing dish.
Keep mixture warm.

title: spinach and rice
directions: Saute onions in oil until soft.
Add tomato paste and spinach and stir.
Add water to cover and bring to boil.
Add seasonings. Sprinkle rice on top but do not stir.
Cover and simmer until rice is cooked.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix orange segments, oil, eggs and cake mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled greens
directions: Put meat in kettle or Dutch oven and add water to cover. Bring to a boil. Simmer and cook for 2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat and cut meat from bones, if necessary. Soak greens to remove sand and grit. Lift greens from water and drain water off so sand goes off with the water. Rinse under running water until all sand is gone. Add greens, pepper and bacon drippings to meat liquid. Arrange meat on top of greens. Simmer for 35 minutes or just until greens can be cut with a fork. Add water if necessary, to prevent sticking. Lift meat and greens from liquid. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: joan's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips. Delicious!

title: "spirited cheese fondue"
directions: In a large saucepan, heat half and half, mustard and Drambuie. Combine cheese and flour.
Gradually beat into liquid.
Cook over low heat, stirring until cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Dip bread, turkey, apple and pear into warm fondue.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and spoon off all excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and put everything else together, except Mozzarella cheese. First:
noodles; second:
cottage filling; third:
the meat sauce. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter together.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Beat egg slightly and add to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamy mixture.
Add more flour if dough is not stiff enough.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Press gently with sugared fork.
This is important to the flavor of the cookies.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, then microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: minted nuts
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup together until rolling boil; then boil exactly one minute.
Take off stove, add marshmallow cream, peppermint and nuts.
Stir in a circular motion until all nuts are coated and mixture hardens.
Cool on wax paper.

title: squash delight
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add garlic, pepper, cheese and pimento.
Stir in butter until melted.
Top with corn chips.
Serves 6.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, gently cook onions, celery and bell pepper in sausage fat.
Cook until softened.
Drain fat.
