title: wilted greens
directions: Melt drippings in heavy pan; add a little chopped onion and cook until soft and yellow.
Stir in vinegar, then add lettuce. Cover and heat a few minutes, until greens are wilted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: moon cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine pudding mix, milk and cream cheese. Mix with electric mixer until smooth. Spread evenly over pie crust. Top with whipped topping and drizzle with chocolate syrup. Chill in refrigerator and serve cold.

title: vegetable barley soup
directions: Place meat, tomatoes, salt and bay leaf in large pan.
Add water, cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Add barley, cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans, corn, oregano and garlic.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Single layer whole crackers on bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk according to package.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour half of the pudding over the crackers. Cover with another layer of crackers.
Pour rest of pudding over crackers.
Cover with another layer of crackers.
Mix together the chocolate, margarine, Karo, sugar, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Spread over crackers.
Do not cover for 1 day in refrigerator. Refrigerate at least 2 days up to 6 days. Better as it stands.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice and bouillon in shallow casserole dish.
Lay pork chops on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken with lemon butter
directions: Mix butter and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until firm.
Dip breast in egg, then bread crumbs.
Put a teaspoon of butter/lemon mix in center of breast.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Fry in oil (corn or olive) until all sides are browned and chicken cooked though.
Remove toothpicks prior to serving.

title: rhubarb with strawberries(microwave)
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and water in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes, until rhubarb is tender and slightly transparent.
Stir in strawberries.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings (115 calories per serving).

title: crescent chicken
directions: Cook the chicken and debone.
Tear apart crescent rolls and place chicken inside.
In a saucepan mix together soup, cheese and butter.
Cook until warm. Pour sauce over rolls and cook on 350° until rolls are brown.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add onions. Saute until pale in color (do not brown).
Add potatoes, water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Cook until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add corn, creamed corn, half and half and milk.
Continue cooking (no cover) on medium heat, 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 cups.
Contains 260 calories per cup.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add last 3.
Mix well.
Keep in refrigerator in covered container (as long as 6 weeks).
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press in bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan.
Beat cheese, sugar and milk until blended and smooth. Spread over crust.
Top with pecans.
Fold vanilla and sugar into whipped cream and spread over nuts.
Combine cherry filling with almond flavoring.
Pour over all.
Chill overnight.

title: toll house walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar; blend in butter and stir in melted chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: like grandma's soft spicy raisin hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in sour cream and eggs until blended.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: golden cream cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrot, onion, parsley flakes, bouillon cube and seasonings; mix well. Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended. Add milk mixture to vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Add processed cheese; stir until melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: Grind enough Vidalia onions to yield 1 1/2 gallons.
Add 1/2 cup salt; let stand 30 minutes.
Squeeze juice from onion-salt mixture; discard juice.
To onions, add vinegar, sugar, spices and pimento.
Bring to a boil; cook for 30 minutes, stirring often. Pack both onions and cooking liquid to cover in hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space.
Remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims.
Adjust lids.
Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Makes about 8 pint jars.

title: diet sunshine carrots
directions: Peel onions; scrape carrots and slice thinly.
Place in saucepan with water to cover.
Cook until water boils.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until vegetables have absorbed all liquid without burning.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter sensation
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in small bowl.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Make crisscross pattern on dough with floured fork. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.

title: peanut butter cup tarts
directions: Spray miniature muffin tins with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°. Refrigerate peanut butter cups to chill so paper will peel off easily.
Follow directions for slicing or cookie wrapper.
Drop a quarter slice in each muffin cup.
Place in oven and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately push an unwrapped peanut butter into each muffin cup.
Cookies will rise and puff out of each cup and make a tart.
Let cool.
Refrigerate.
Makes 36.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in the 2 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Combine in a bowl with the canned chicken and green chili peppers.
Set aside.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Let cool. Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: hot cocoa mix(for children)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container. Yields 2 1/3 cup mix.
Add 2/3 cups boiling water to 1/3 cup hot cocoa mix.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually add sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin and vanilla.
Pour into prepared shell.
Bake for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Put 2 tablespoons pineapple syrup, egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, butter and salt in a small pan.
Heat on low and stir until mixture thickens slightly (about 10 minutes).
Cool.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries in food chopper.
Chop apples.
Add juice of oranges, pineapple, pecans and sugar.
Mix well and keeps up to 2 to 3 weeks in fridge.
Good at Christmastime.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Night before sprinkle with salt; pour liquid smoke over and turn several times to marinate real well.
Cover well and refrigerate.

title: eclair cake
directions: Make layer of graham crackers on bottom of a 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Mix pudding.
Add Cool Whip as the pudding thickens.
Put 1/2 of pudding mixture on crackers, then another layer of crackers. Pour rest of pudding; end up with crackers on top.

title: apple crunch
directions: Combine oats, flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Place 1/2 of mixture in bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Spoon on apple pie filling or spread out apple slices.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
You can double this recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all together.
Like pancake batter. Heat oil in a pan and spoon batter in.
Fry on low.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; beat until smooth.
Stir in grated carrots. Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Ice when completely cool.

title: chicken breasts dijon
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish; stir well and set aside.
Brush mustard and blend evenly over both sides of chicken.
Dredge chicken with bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish coated with the vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: aunt cheryl's chilli
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
If still thick, add more water. (Great on hot dogs and burgers.)
(Leftovers:
Can add your favorite items for chilli beans or spaghetti sauce.)

title: best ever banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake until top is golden brown and splits slightly, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Great with cream cheese.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 3 (8-inch) skillets.
Bake at 325° until cake is done.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, breadcrumbs, soup mix and eggs.
Form into meatballs.
Place in roaster.
Combine chili sauce, sauerkraut, water, whole cranberry sauce and brown sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the meatballs.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti italian salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directions say.
Rinse with cold water and then hot water until all thick look is gone and it's slick and shiny.
Mix all ingredients together and let set in refrigerator for a few hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Boil potatoes until tender. Drain and pour in buttered dish.
In pan boil milk and cheeses. Pour on top of potatoes.
Top with pimento and bell pepper.
Bake in 350° oven until green peppers are tender, about 25 minutes.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Clean shrimp; drain.
Chill for 1 hour and mince thoroughly. In a mixing bowl, mix shrimp, garlic, onion, salt, pepper and egg white.
Spread shrimp mixture over slice of bread.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds and deep-fry.
Lower into oil with shrimp side down. After 1 minute, turn over and fry until golden brown.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put margarine and cream cheese in a 9 x 13-inch glass microwave dish and cook 2 to 3 minutes on High, until melted. Depending on microwave, may take longer to melt cream cheese.
Add dry mixture and vanilla.
When all dry mixture is blended in, then add walnuts.
Use your hands to mix up the fudge and press out in pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in unsalted water until barely tender. Cook chicken with no salt. Layer broccoli then chicken in a greased baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken and broccoli. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sour milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Add a little more flour if needed.
Put on floured board and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.
When cool, frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: phyliss' chicken salad
directions: Cut and put above fruit, nuts and cubed chicken together. Mix mayonnaise with curry powder and stir into fruit and meat. Adjust the amounts of fruit, chicken, and mayonnaise according to personal taste.

title: pork chop glaze
directions: Cook cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce and apricot juice over heat until it thickens.
Prepare Stove Top dressing mix according to package.
Bake pork chops for 30 minutes or so in oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in a large casserole dish.
Mix in 1/2 can French fried onions and carrots.
Place potato slices in casserole with edge up.
Dot Velveeta cubes in casserole with butter.
Pour 1/2 cup milk over casserole.
Salt and pepper to season.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Pour remaining onions over top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage meat.
Reserve fat.
Shred cheese.
Combine cheese and sausage.
Stretch dough into a rectangle about the size of cookie sheet.
Spread with mixture.
Fold over (half over half). Pinch seams.
Brush with reserved grease.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden.
(Cut into slices before reheating.) Makes 1 loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Heat until smooth.
Defrost broccoli (do not cook).
Add broccoli to above mixture.
Then add mushrooms, water chestnuts and rice to cheese mixture.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put spices in cheesecloth, tied up. Cut up pickles in large mixing bowl. Add sugar, vinegar and pickling spice. Store in refrigerator, stirring until sugar dissolves. Put in jars. Keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate slowly in 2 tablespoons liquid cream.
Chill this mixture to lukewarm and stir in egg yolk.
Whip remaining cream and mix carefully with chocolate mixture.
Beat egg whites firmly and mix in carefully.
Chill in refrigerator for 4 to 5 hours.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add Miracle Whip and water.
Beat all ingredients about 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Take wax paper and sprinkle with coconut.
Add mixture and roll.
Refrigerate 8 hours.
Slice.
Makes 3 rolls.

title: onion spread with giant crackers
directions: In a mixing bowl, smoothly blend Ricotta, eggs, dill, salt and pepper.
Add chopped green onions.
Stir to mix.
Spoon mixture into a 9 or 10-inch microsafe pie pan (or other round-sided dish with 1 1/2 to 2-inch high sides).
Smooth out into an even layer. Microwave, uncovered, at Medium-low power for 20 minutes, rotating dish a quarter turn 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Cover with paper towel.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Center of cheese spread should be firm when gently touched.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes longer, if necessary.
Let cool in pan at least 1 hour or cool completely. Cover and refrigerate as long as 2 days.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine buttermilk, butter and eggs until blended.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make well in center.
Add buttermilk mixture.
Stir until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in prepared 400° oven for 20 minutes or until tops are golden and toothpick in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool on wire rack.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: english bread & butter pudding
directions: Spread the butter onto the slices of bread, the crusts may be removed if desired. Cut into fingers or small squares.

Line the bottom of a 1 qt. buttered casserole dish with bread. Sprinkle currants, then sugar over the bread. Repeat the layers ending with bread, buttered side up. Beat the eggs and milk together and pour over the bread. Sprinkle with nutmeg, leave to stand for about 30 minutes to allow the bread to absorb some of the liquid. Then bake at 325°f.
160°c. gas mark 3 for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until pudding is set and the top is crisp and golden. Serve hot or cold with fresh cream. Serves 4.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add pineapple and juice and eggs. Mix.
Then pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Top with 3/4 cup brown sugar and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave cauliflower
directions: Combine cauliflower with water.
Cover tightly and microwave until crisp-tender (about 6 to 9 minutes) the vinaigrette of raspberry, vinegar, raspberry preserves, oil and parsley to taste. Season with salt and pepper.
Drizzle over cauliflower.

title: manuella's artichoke balls
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Add bread crumbs, cheese and eggs.
Let stand.
Chop garlic fine; saute in oil until soft.
Add mixtures.
Stir until heated all over.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in extra crumbs and cheese.

title: glazed grapefruit
directions: Cut grapefruit in half; cut around sections.
Place in glass serving bowl.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over grapefruit and dot with margarine.
Pour 1 teaspoon orange juice over each half.
Microwave for 6 to 7 minutes on High or until warm.
Garnish with cherries.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins 20 minutes in 2 cups water, stir in shortening, and add one cup of cold water.
Sift all dry ingredients together except the soda and add to the raisin mixture.
Dissolve 1 level tablespoon soda in 1 tablespoon boiling water and add to the batter.
Pour into tube pan and bake 350° for 1 hour.
Do not over bake.
The cake should be at least a day old before serving to obtain full flavor.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: quail in trenchers
directions: Scoop centers of rolls out.
Butter and sprinkle with garlic powder and toast.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat all liquids along with onion, put juice from baking chicken in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Then put a layer of cut tortillas and a layer of chicken and a layer of liquid.
Repeat these three layers again and top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until bubbly.

title: joe stuckey's own chili
directions: Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in skillet.
Add the cubed beef and simmer until gray.
Meanwhile in a 6-quart pot, place 1 quart water, beef bouillon and bay leaves.
Turn heat to high.
When cubed beef is gray (to brown color), add to pot, then in turn, brown ground pork in skillet and add to pot.
Then brown ground beef in skillet and add to pot.

title: garlic roasted vegetables
directions: Combine, in a large bowl, the oil, lemon peel, salt, pepper, rosemary, potatoes, garlic, onions and red pepper.
Toss well. Spread in jelly roll pan.
Roast at 450° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza dog
directions: Boil hot dog until almost done.
Slice down the middle and add 2 to 3 teaspoons of sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in preheated 325° oven until cheese is melted.
Remove tomato sauce from can and refrigerate leftovers.

title: finger quiche(appetizer)
directions: In large bowl, combine in order given.
Grease 9 x 11 or 9 x 13-inch dish with 2 1/2 teaspoons margarine.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Cool slightly.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
These can be frozen and reheated in microwave.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, Milnot, eggs, cinnamon and sugar and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture. Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix. Sprinkle pecans over butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab stew
directions: Saute the green onions, onion and green pepper in the oil in a large skillet until tender.
Add the water.
Simmer until the mixture is hot.
Stir in the roux mix.
Simmer on low for 15 minutes or until the mixture thickens.
Stir in the seasonings, shrimp and crab meat.
Simmer, partially covered, over low heat for 10 minutes or until the shrimp turn pink.
Serve over rice or hollowed-out fried pistollette rolls.
Leftovers may be frozen. Yields 6 servings.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Then add barbecue sauce and stir.
Let simmer.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, bananas and flour mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips if wanted.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: crab puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating until very stiff.
Combine mayonnaise, crabmeat, chives and peppers in another bowl.
Fold into whites, blending well.

title: microwave granola
directions: Microwave oats in large dish
on High for 2 minutes. Meantime, combine all dry ingredients.
Mix oil, honey and vanilla together.
Remove oats and combine with dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add liquid mixture, stirring until well blended. Roast in microwave for 13 minutes, stirring several times.
Remove from oven.
Cool and stir occasionally to break up granola.
When cool, place in covered container.
Serve with milk, adding raisins, if desired.
Delicious with ice cream or yogurt!

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Put yeast in warm water.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients in order.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Save some for top.
Blend thawed orange juice with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and oranges.
Do not beat.
Pour mixture over crust.
Top with reserved crumbs and a few slices of oranges. Refrigerate or freeze until serving.

title: eleanor's carrot cake
directions: Stir eggs, oil, vanilla, walnut flavor and sugar all together.
Add cinnamon, flour, carrots and walnuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: orange-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Pare sweet potatoes, cut each in half lengthwise and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In small saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and orange peel.
Stir in orange juice and butter and cook until thick.
Pour over the sweet potatoes and bake, covered, about 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: christmas nibblings
directions: Melt grease and oleo and add seasonings.
Pour over other ingredients and mix well.
Mix often while baking in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours at 200°.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: fruit cake
directions: Makes 2 tube pound cakes.
Cook approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°.
Make sure to place a pan of water in oven while cooking.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: irish potato stew
directions: Brown cubes in kettle.
Add about 7 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove scum; add 2 teaspoons salt, chopped onion, cut carrots, quartered, peeled potatoes and fresh or dried parsley. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat and shred.
Mash the potato and carrots.
Place back into the kettle.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until completely moistened. Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Fill 1/2 to 2/3 with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Yields 12 to 14 muffins.

title: grandma's cherry cake dessert
directions: Mix sour cream, water and eggs.
Stir in cake mix.
Spread in a jellyroll pan (cookie sheet with 1-inch sides).
Drop cherry pie filling on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
tags: Betty Crocker sour cream white cake

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a long 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with 3/4 cup buttered crumbs.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kahlua
directions: Pour vodka into a dark bottle. Combine coffee, sugar, cocoa and water in saucepan. Make a simple syrup (cook until the mixture is the consistency of maple syrup). Cool completely and pour into a bottle. Quarter the vanilla bean and add to the bottle. Seal and put the bottle in a cool dark place for at least a month. Shake bottle once a week.

title: caramel crunch ice cream dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix brown sugar, flour, oats, pecans and butter together in a jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 minutes. Crumble while hot.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Line muffin pans with paper. Drop a little chocolate (melted in double boiler) in each paper liner.
Then add 1 tablespoon peanut butter mixture, then more chocolate chips on top.

title: four bean bake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for a couple of hours or in a crock-pot for a long time.

title: hot artichoke hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in an ovenproof casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes,
until bubbly.
Add a dash of paprika on top for color and serve with crackers. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Bake in a 15 1/2
X
11 inch pan that is greased and floured at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chilled cranberry soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine cranberries, water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until about half of the cranberries are popped.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and orange peel.
Cool.
Cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours.
Before serving, remove cinnamon stick.
Serve in soup bowls.
If desired, garnish with fresh mint.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into glass pan (9 x 13-inch). Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzels.
Refrigerate.
Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
When it starts to congeal, add strawberries. Spread Jell-O over other mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese mexican chicken
directions: Mix the tomatoes and green chiles with the soup in a large skillet. Add the cheese and chicken. Cook until the cheese melts, stirring constantly. Place the vermicelli in a greased casserole dish. Pour the chicken and cheese mixture over the vermicelli. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and cut in cubes.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Mix soups, mayonnaise, cheese and chicken together in a large bowl.
Add Rice-A-Roni and broccoli to mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice dinner
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat. Cover and boil gently, about 25 minutes until rice is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: In small saucepan place peanut butter chips, milk and whipping cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Serve warm.
Cover; refrigerate leftover sauce.
Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake, covered, for 45 minutes, then uncovered for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer salsa on top of cheese mixture.
Top with layers of chopped onion, Cheddar cheese, chopped tomato and shredded lettuce.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with taco chips or Doritos.

title: leftover chicken supreme
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish, alternate 2 layers each of chicken, onions and noodles.
Combine soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour over layers.
Combine pecans and margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter. Add flour, half at a time. Pat into greased 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl combine butter, sugar, flour, cereal, baking soda and salt.
Beat at low speed until mixture is blended.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Meanwhile, in saucepan combine caramels and milk.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
When bars are removed from oven, drizzle caramel mixture over top.
Yield:
36 bars.

title: smoky bacon wraps
directions: Cut each bacon strip into thirds.
Wrap one piece of bacon around each sausage.
Place in a foil lined 15x10 inch baking pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered at 400 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: squid rings
directions: Clean the squid, removing skin and head.
Cut into rings about 1/8-inch thick.
Squeeze lemon over the squid, then wash thoroughly.
Drain; add salt and white pepper.
Roll lightly in cornstarch.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: light chicken divan
directions: Brown the chicken in the oil until cooked, about 5 minutes. Add the broccoli, water, wine and soup and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Add dry ingredients, lastly apples, raisins and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350°.
Ice with caramel icing.

title: cheese supper bread
directions: Stir together until barely mixed the milk, egg, Bisquick and 1 cup of the cheese.
Spread the dough in a 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle dough with poppy seed, the remaining cheese and the melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until medium brown.

title: maple oat crispies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add molasses, maple extract and eggs; blend well.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in oats, rice cereal and chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheets.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Simmer 1 cup berries and 2/3 cup water until berries boil and start to break up (about 3 minutes).
Blend cornstarch, sugar and remaining 1/3 cup water and add to boiling mixture.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Place remaining 3 cups berries in baked pie crust; cover with cooked mixture. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
(I tint with red food color.)

title: rolls
directions: In a large bowl, put the Crisco and sugar; blend together.
Add hot water and stir until dissolved, then add cold water and a little salt.
Add enough flour to make a paste.
Add eggs and mix. Add yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add to mixture.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cut out and let rise 2 hours.

title: good-for-you beef stroganoff
directions: Cook No Yolk noodles according to package directions without salt.
Meanwhile, cut beef across grain into 2 x 1/2-inch strips. Cook meat in large nonstick skillet over medium heat until browned.
Remove and reserve meat.
Drain and discard any liquid in skillet.
Add water to skillet.
Stir in onions and mushrooms; saute until tender.
Add catsup, mustard and pepper.
Drain noodles.
Add noodles, reserved meat and yogurt mixture to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally; do not boil. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: marzipans(strawberry design)
directions: Chop coconut and nuts real fine in blender. Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: faye's chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes and serve over Chinese noodles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all; pour into sprayed pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender. Blend until it resembles chunky-style peanut butter.
Pour into jar and keep in refrigerator.
Shake before using.
(Keeps a long time.)

title: stuffed bread
directions: Brown beef and sausage and drain off approximately half of the fat.
Add the inside of Italian bread (broken into small pieces). Add carrots, cut small and cooked.
Add potatoes, cooked and mashed.
Mix all of the ingredients and season to taste with the following:
Italian seasoning, oregano, parsley flakes and garlic. To help hold together, add hot water with bouillon cubes.
Stuff Italian bread with this meat mixture.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Try 1 teaspoon baking powder or try 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
You know how to put a cake together!

title: green beans for a bunch
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or comparable size casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so until heated through.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Test for doneness.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cut eggs in halves and remove yolks.
Mash yolks and blend mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Combine the remaining ingredients and fold into cubed potatoes.
Delicious served hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and drain.
Add pizza sauce.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with pepperoni and sausage.
Sprinkle 2 cups cheese on top. Beat eggs, milk, oil, flour and salt.
Pour over mixture. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on.
Bake in oven 45 minutes at 400°.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften cheese and margarine.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients, except muffins.
Spread thin coating on each muffin half.
(May be frozen at this point to use later.) Place muffin halves on cookie sheet and brown under broiler.
Cut each into quarters.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: mike's special sandwiches
directions: Saute sliced green onions and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Meanwhile, slice cheese and avocado.
Spread outside of slices of sourdough bread with a small amount of butter.
Heat griddle and place bread on griddle with the buttered side down and place onion/mushroom mixture and sliced cheese and avocado on bread.
Top with another slice of bread and lightly brown both sides of sandwich. This sandwich is best served hot.

title: chili beans
directions: Pick out bad beans and wash.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain, then put into crock-pot.
Cover again with cold water.
Cook on low until tender.
Fry hamburger meat and onion until meat is lightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add meat mixture to beans and cook slow another 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Add salt if needed.

title: stir-fry chicken and peppers
directions: Marinate chicken 20 minutes in sherry and soy sauce.
Heat wok with oil.
Add minced ginger root and garlic.
Stir-fry chicken until lightly brown.
Remove from wok.
Add green peppers.
Cook with onions, then add mushrooms.
Finally, add back chicken.
Add cornstarch to broth.
Add to wok to thicken.
Serve with rice.

title: tuna salad supper
directions: Combine
all ingredients; mix with salad dressing.
Two fresh tomatoes may be cut up and added if desired.

title: creamy punch
directions: Spoon ice cream in punch bowl.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Stir with large spoon.
Slowly add soda.
Punch is very foamy.
Serves 25.

title: chili con queso
directions: Put all ingredients into 3-quart saucepan and melt over medium-low heat, stirring often.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon-yogurt scones
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Blend in butter until crumbly. Combine yogurt and lemon zest, stir into flour mixture until just blended. Turn onto floured surface and flatten into a round about 1 inch thick. Cut into 8-10 wedges. Place onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12-14 minutes at 425°.

title: swedish pork chops
directions: Mix
salt,
pepper,
ginger and flour.
Dust chops with mixture.
In
heavy skillet, brown chops lightly on both sides in hot oil.
Lower heat and cook until done, about 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, vanilla, and eggs together with mixer. Set aside. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Combine with first mixture. Fold in oats and walnuts. Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 350 degrees oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields about 3 dozens.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan. Saute meat and onion until brown. Add soup and corn. Mix thoroughly. Put in a greased baking dish. Cover with potatoes. Brush top with egg yolk. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

In a square or round casserole dish, layer the following: rye bread or Triscuits, pour 1/4 cup sauerkraut juice over it, add sauerkraut to cover bread, add slices of kielbasa, add Swiss cheese. Repeat: bread/Triscuits, juice, sauerkraut, kielbasa, Swiss cheese.
Cover with lid or foil and bake 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix ice cream and sour cream together.
Prepare jello using boiling water (juice from apricots may be used as part of water). Cool.
Add jello to ice cream and sour cream, small amounts at a time.
Mix.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and 1/2 cup chopped onion.
Add taco sauce and heat.
Blend in chili powder, salt, Tabasco sauce and kidney beans.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle over top 1/2 cup chopped onion, 1/2 cup green olives and 1 cup or more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: praline cookies
directions: Line cookie sheets with foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place graham crackers on foil lined pan with sides touching.
Melt sugar and butter and cook to rolling boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour over crackers and bake for 10 minutes. Cool 15 minutes and peel crackers from foil.

title: postre de ciruelas y vino
directions: Put plums in wine a day before making recipe.
Do not refrigerate.
Remove pits and place on stove with wine.
Cook until it becomes like a stewed fruit.
Remove and let cool.
Whip egg whites until hardened.
Add sugar, heavy cream and plum mixture.
Dissolve the gelatine in hot water.
When dissolved, add to mixture.
Pour into a greased baking pan with a hole in the center.
Place in refrigerator until thickened and set.
Use a knife to cut in pieces.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Remove cake from oven and immediately poke holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake (I only use about 3/4 of the can).
Cool completely.
After cake is completely cool, pour caramel topping over cake (about 3/4 of jar).
Spread Cool Whip on cake and then sprinkle crushed Heath bar over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: montezuma pie
directions: Drain canned chilies and reserve the juice.
Mix together chilies, onion, parsley and chopped jalapeno chilies if desired. Saute chili mixture in butter and oil for 3 minutes in a 10-inch skillet.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken stock and any reserved juices from the canned chilies.
Add salt and remove from heat and set aside.
Combine sour cream and Ricotta cheese and set aside. Quarter 4 of the tortillas.
Heat about 1/4-inch of oil to 350° in a medium skillet.
Immerse the 6 whole tortillas one at a time, in the oil for a few seconds until softened, but not crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Add additional oil and raise heat to 375°.
Fry tortilla quarters until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve the quarters for garnish.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the oil, eggs and sugar in one bowl and the dry ingredients in a separate bowl. Add the dry ingredients to the liquids and mix well.
Stir in 3 cups apples and 1 cup pecans. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: house tea
directions: Dissolve instant tea and lemonade mix in hot water, about 3 cups.
Combine all other ingredients and stir well.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts together until thick.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of cake comes clean.
Cool for 10 minutes on a rack, then remove from pan.
You may frost with whipped cream if desired.
It's very rich.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Dilute	frozen juices following directions on can.
Mix with pineapple juice and sugar.

title: chicken diable
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Melt margarine in shallow baking pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture to coat both sides, then arrange meat side up, in a single layer in the same pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and cream alternately and finally the vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chili stew enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain and add chopped chilies, garlic and enough water or broth to make a stew-like consistency.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Lightly fry tortillas until soft.
Place small amount of shredded cheese and chopped onion in each tortilla and roll.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour chili stew over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with additional cheese and onion.
Cover and heat in oven until cheese melts, about 8 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: busy wife biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine other dry ingredients.
When yeast is dissolved, add all liquids to flour mixture.
Work into a smooth dough, kneading for 5 minutes. Biscuits may be formed and baked immediately or stored in a covered bowl (in refrigerator) and baked as needed.
This dough may be used for pizza crust.
Turn over crust wrapped around wieners and baked or for any variety of cobbler.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and form crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with sour cream. Add enough chopped onion to cover.
Arrange sliced olives over onion.
Chop fresh tomato over this.
Cover with a layer of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle taco sauce over this.
Heat in a 350° oven until cheese melts.
Good with nachos or Doritos.

title: diet pasta salad
directions: Boil the pasta until done and drain.
Open English peas and drain.
Mix all the ingredients, then pour salad dressing over it. Serve.

title: lo-cal vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over rice.
Spoon celery soup over evenly.
Pour in 2 cups of water and place chicken on top.
Cook, uncovered, on 400° for 20 minutes, then cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no fail chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Mix ingredients in saucepan and cook slowly until thickens. Remove from pan, add vanilla and butter. Pour into an 8-inch baked pie crust. Cool and top with whipped cream before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda; cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir just until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: recipe for meringue
directions: Never use any plastic utensils.
In a glass or stainless steel mixing bowl (clean, grease-free, dry; beaters, too), beat the egg whites on medium speed until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue over fillings, sealing edges to crusts.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
Meringue covering for 9-inch pie, etc.

title: pickled hot banana peppers
directions: Put turmeric, garlic, alum and oil into each sterilized jar. Add banana peppers and pack in tightly.
Make a brine of the water, vinegar and salt; bring to boil and pour over peppers. Seal jars.
After a week, turn jars upside down for a week before storing.

title: sirloin tip marinade
directions: Combine dressings.
Marinate roast in same for 2 days in the refrigerator.
Turn occasionally.
Charcoal 20 minutes on each side and slice thin.

title: blue woo-woo
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve over crushed ice. Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Mix ingredients with cooked vermicelli and refrigerate overnight or all day.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over fruit of your choosing.
I prefer to mix pineapple chunks, fruit cocktail, apples, bananas and grapes.

title: quick spinach quiche
directions: Thaw one 10-inch deep-dish pie crust.
Grate 1/4 to 1/3 Swiss cheese into the pie crust bottom.
Spread the thawed or barely cooked frozen spinach on top of the cheese.
Do not mix.
Add the chopped onions, nutmeg and basil.
Whisk the eggs in the milk and pour over the top of the mixture.
Sprinkle paprika over top and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: niebruegge dish
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain off grease.
Boil noodles 10 minutes and drain.
Add grated cheese to meat and onions.
Then add tomatoes to mixture; add to noodles.
Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken mushroom bake
directions: Brown chicken in butter until done. Remove chicken from pan. Add remaining ingredients and cook for 15 minutes on low heat. Add chicken to pan and serve over white rice.

title: autumn festival fluff
directions: Combine graham cracker, brown sugar, 1/2 cup peanut butter and butter.
Mix well with fork until crumbly.
Press 2/3 of crumbs into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Reserve remaining crumbs for topping.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture over crust.
Spread apple pie filling over cheese fluff.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon if desired.
Combine confectioners sugar and 1/3 cup peanut butter with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over apples. Top with remaining cheese fluff, then sprinkle with remaining graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter crumbs.
Cover with foil. Refrigerate full 24 hours before serving.

title: quick taco bean soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add the rest of the ingredients with all liquids in the cans.
Extra water may be added if too thick.
Simmer until well heated.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco, margarine and sugar well.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or longer.
Cool for a few minutes before removing from pan.
Frost with your favorite fudge frosting.

title: low carb hamburger casserole ole
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°. Brown the beef and drain the excess fat. Add the taco mix and water; cook over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until the liquid has been absorbed.

Add the diced tomatoes and black beans. Meanwhile, cook the green beans according to the package directions and drain. Spread the meat mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Spread the beans over the meat. Sprinkle with the cheeses. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until hot and cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice as directed.
Add other ingredients and bake in casserole dish.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cook sauerkraut and tomato sauce together for 3 minutes.
In pan, brown sausage and onions in bacon fat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to make it tan.
Mix sauerkraut, mushrooms, beans and soup mix in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Add sausage and onion mixture and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
(Can substitute hot dogs or ham if you wish.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients.
Stir yogurt, pineapple, Egg Beaters and oil into flour mixture.
Stir in raisins, carrots and walnuts. Pour batter into floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: danish pork roast
directions: Mix together salt and spices; rub mixture into surface of roast.
Refrigerate overnight.
Combine fruits, cinnamon and Grand Marnier, brandy or apple juice.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Wash and core lettuce.
Pare and section oranges.
Peel and slice bananas.
Slice or halve dates.
Combine lettuce chunks and half the fruit in large chilled serving bowl.
Arrange remaining fruit on top.
When ready to serve, toss with Ambrosia Dressing. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Marinate 24 hours before serving.
Can substitute Seven Seas dressing.

title: crabcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into cakes.
Fry in small amount of hot oil.

title: vegetable 'n pasta salad
directions: Heat water, vinegar, sugar and dry mustard and let cool.
Cook mixed vegetables according to directions on package.
Cook pasta until done.
Combine vegetables and pasta.
Add kidney beans, onion, peppers, seasoning, parsley and ground pepper.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
Better if made the day before serving.

title: jewel candies
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with foil, extending foil up sides; butter foil.
Butter sides of heavy 1-quart saucepan; add sugar, corn syrup and water, mixing well.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook over medium heat to 300° (hard crack stage).
Remove from heat; add flavored oil and food coloring.
Pour into prepared pan at once.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Mix in dry cake mix and stir until cake mix is all moist.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle all the chocolate chips (morsels) over the cake batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip and enjoy!

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Add pieces of chicken and broth to mix.
Add 1 tablespoon black pepper.
Pour into crock-pot and cook 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Stir vigorously with fork 1 minute.
Spread in pan.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook shell macaroni.
Place macaroni in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour on Ragu sauce.
Do not stir.
Put on cooked sausage.
Place in oven and cook at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Put back in oven for 5 more minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and soda. Combine and beat eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Stir egg mixture into dry ingredients. Beat 3 minutes with electric mixer on slow speed. Pour into cake pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: norwegian lefsetortilla-like flat bread
directions: Mix all ingredients using enough flour to make a soft dough. On a floured board, roll small balls of dough into pie-crust-size circles.
Use enough flour for each Lefse to keep from sticking to the rolling pin and board.

title: orange carrot cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add carrots, flour, baking powder and salt together; blend to mixture.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, frost with Orange Frosting.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 pies.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze out well.
Mix together ingredients and let stand a while for flavors to blend.

title: loretta lynn's square dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and beaten eggs with enough milk to make stiff dough.
Roll out a little thicker than a pie crust.
Cut into squares.
Let stand a little while to puff.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: May use any flavor jello.

title: mexican cornbread 1
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix together well.
Pour half of the mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 can chilies over cornmeal mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over the top and add 1/2 cup grated cheese and the other half of the green chilies.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet 9 day pickles
directions: Wash and cube cucumbers.
Cover with boiling water and let stand until next day.
Repeat this process for 4 days.
Pour off water and rinse carefully after each time.
On fifth day, combine other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over pickles and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Reheat.
Put cubed cucumbers into hot jars. Pour juice over and seal.
If you do not want to can; place in plastic containers and put into ice box.
(Stays good for a long time.)

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Mix sifted dry ingredients and nuts together.
Combine egg, applesauce and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Pour into a 9-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large sauce pan.
Cook until thick and will spin a thread.
While this is cooking, beat two egg whites until they are fluffy.
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites beating constantly with a mixer.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts. Beat with spoon until firm enough to drop on waxed paper. Add food coloring if desired.

title: baked stuffed clams
directions: In large skillet, arrange clams and add 1/2 inch water.
Cook covered over medium high heat for 5 minutes or until clams open. Remove clams, reserving 3/4 c. liquid, strain liquid.
Remove clams from shells, then chip clams, keep shell halves.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Mix well.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture and put in greased pan.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Very good!

title: bagels
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1 tablespoon salt and yeast.
Heat 1 1/2 cups water and the margarine to 120° or 130°.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in more flour to make stiff dough.
On floured board, knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Set in greased bowl.
Turn to grease top; cover.
Let rise in warm, draft-free place 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Cover. Let rest 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti with sherried mushroom sauce
directions: In medium saucepan combine mushrooms, onion, garlic, sherry, peppers, red pepper flakes, coriander and allspice.
Cover and cook until vegetables are softened, 5 to 6 minutes.
Chop tomatoes and add with juice; simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
Transfer to a serving dish; toss with olive oil.
Stir basil and parsley into tomato sauce and either toss with spaghetti or pour over spaghetti. Serves 4; contains 310 calories per serving.

title: chunky chicken soup
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onions, green peppers, carrots and garlic in oil until tender. Add chicken broth, tomatoes, kidney beans, cooked chicken and basil. Cook 10 minutes. Stir in shell pasta. Cook 10 more minutes. Serve with shredded Parmesan. Serves 4.

title: cookie pie
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Work like pie crust.
Add sugar and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, milk and eggs.

title: play dough
directions: Put dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add liquids and stir with wooden spoon until dough pulls away from sides of bowl. Knead dough as it cools.
Store in airtight containers.

title: orange-angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water.
Add orange juice, then sugar.
Mix and cool.
Whip the cream.
Add to first mixture.
Break up angel food cake and add to the mixture. Refrigerate for 24 hours after adding the cake.
(Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: my favorite biscuit recipe
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, cream of tartar and sugar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once and stir until dough just follows fork around bowl. Pat or roll 1/2-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 350°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown chopped onion in oil.
Add chopped celery, parsley, basil and carrots and brown together for a few minutes.
Add chopped meat; stir and cook 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Vermouth and heat 15 minutes on low flame, stirring occasionally.

title: jalapeno pepper bread
directions: Mix all and pour into well greased 10-1/2 inch skillet. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Stir over low heat until shortening and chocolate are melted, stirring constantly.
Bring rapidly to a full rolling boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring and continue beating until icing begins to lose its gloss.
(Considerable beating is required.)
If icing does not stiffen after 30 minutes, add 1 teaspoon confectioners sugar.
If too stiff, add 1 teaspoon of milk.

title: fruit loaf
directions: Mix all together. Pour in pan and put in refrigerator.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in crock-pot. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.

title: economy dinner
directions: Place bacon strips on bottom of covered 2-quart casserole dish.
Add thick ground beef patties on top of this.
Add sliced onions, potatoes and carrots.
Layer until amount desired.
Salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Drain oil off after 30 minutes cooking time.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix taco seasoning with drained ground beef.
Layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put 1/2 of cheese.
Then layer mashed potatoes and top with remaining cheese.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.
Easy!

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Make your favorite recipe for pie crust.
Roll out and cut in small rounds to fit cupcake tins.
Add 1/2 teaspoon real strawberry jam (not jelly) to each tart crust, then add filling to 3/4 full and bake at 375° until lightly browned or 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool, then frost with frosting and top with 1/2 maraschino cherry in center.

title: roger's chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into segments and brown in butter.
Remove chicken and brown mushrooms, onion, green pepper and garlic in same pan.
In a large sauce pan pour tomatoes and all other ingredients except chicken and noodles.
Bring to a boil.
Then add chicken and wine.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles
and drain.
Toss noodles with sauce and arrange around chicken to serve.

title: blueberry crumble
directions: In a bowl, combine blueberries, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and lemon peel. Stir to coat thoroughly and set aside. Combine flour and brown sugar.

Add margarine and cut in with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in walnuts. Pour blueberries into a 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with crumb mixture. Bake at 325° until topping is browned and blueberries are bubbly. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and flavoring. Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together. Add to cream mixture.
Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut. Drop by small spoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese and bacon.
Remove stems from mushrooms and stuff with cheese mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes, then brown under broiler.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into squares and boil until tender.
Combine soups, broth, stuffing and mushrooms together.
Spray the bottom of a casserole dish with Baker's Joy and layer mixture with chicken in the dish.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread on a hamburger bun. Add ham and Swiss cheese.
Wrap in foil and bake at 275° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.
Make into balls and dip in melted chocolate.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Drain peas.
Combine ingredients in order given in buttered glass baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in small pieces.
In medium bowl, mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
In large bowl, mix pudding and milk; add cream cheese mixture and Cool Whip to pudding.
Stir until smooth.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in half of the water and add 2 cups of the flour.
Make a sponge and let raise.
When fully raised, add the salt dissolved in the rest of the water and knead with the rest of the flour.
Let raise once the shape in long loaves, place in a baking tin with the seam on the bottom, then cover with a towel and let raise.
When raised, take a very sharp knife and cut 3 small long gashes across the loaf to sever the crust, then place quickly in a hot oven (450°).
When 1/2 baked, wash with milk and finish baking.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix together hash browns (thawed), 1 stick margarine (melted), sour cream, cream of chicken soup, onion flakes, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Spread in a baking dish.
Coarsely crush the Post Toasties.
Mix them in a small bowl with 1 stick melted margarine.
Spread over the potato mixture. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: pipiton apple pie
directions: Prepare and roll out your pie crust.
Line it in a 9 inch pie plate with half the pie crust.

title: chocolate brownies(for the health conscious chocolate lover)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly and set aside.
Blend next 5 ingredients together.
Blend both mixtures together then fold in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 24 minutes.

title: chicken that's special
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Arrange broccoli in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.

title: coal miners cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with any frosting.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix cooked brown and wild rice with chopped onions, bell peppers, and cooked sausages.
Pour in baking pan and cover.
Bake at 250 for 30 minutes.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, garlic, basil leaves, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir into apples.
Turn into pie crust.
Combine remaining flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
If pie browns too quickly, cover edge with foil.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Combine margarine, flour, sugar and nuts in mixing bowl; mix well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: arroz con dulce - candy like rice
directions: In a sauce pan with sufficient water to cover put the cinnamon, anis, cloves and ginger root. Boil to a dark brownish color.Remove the seeds and ginger and cinnamon and mix the water with the coconut milk and the carnation milk. Using a large sauce pan add the milk mixture to the sugar, salt, and raisins. Bring to a boil for just a minute or two, put the rice in and lower your heat. Stir until mixture begins to thicken. It will be done when the mixture no longer can fall off the spoon. Serve in small plates with a dusting of cinnamon.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a 4 1/2 x 8-inch glass loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: diabetic strawberry trifle
directions: Clean and mash berries.
Tear cake into 1-inch cubes.
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Line bowl with a layer of cake, berries and pudding.
Continue layering.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Melt margarine and add onion and celery.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add pimentos, dill weed, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Toss with green beans.
Serves 4.

title: eagle brand cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon juice, milk and pie filling.
Add drained pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill thoroughly.

title: greek salad and vinaigrette
directions: Combine lettuces, vegetables and shrimp in large salad bowl. Toss to combine.
Add enough Vinaigrette to moisten; toss to coat pieces evenly.
Garnish with Feta cheese and anchovy fillets. Refrigerate any unused dressing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into loaf pan.
Hollow top slightly and pour on 1/2 cup of catsup.
Bake 45 minutes or longer at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini and onions for 20 min. Combine with soup, sour cream, carrots and croutons. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded cheese just before you take it out.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and garlic on beef.
Sprinkle half of cheese on this.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to directions.
Rinse and cool.
Chop pepper, tomato and cucumber.
Add Italian dressing; let marinate for 1/2 hour.
Add linguine mix.
Add Salad Supreme.
Mix as you add spice.
If you would like more or different vegetables, use at your discretion.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the pumpkin, eggs, sugar and evaporated milk.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle the melted margarine and sprinkle the pecans over the dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
Cool several hours to set bottom layer.

title: french-style coffee mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly covered jar. To use, add 2 rounded tablespoons of mix to 3/4 cup of boiling water.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and drain the potatoes.
Mash (whip) them to make the 2 cups.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into raw pie shell. Bake at 350°.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Cut the cucumbers in 1-inch chunks and soak in lime mixed with 1 1/2 gallons of water; let stand 24 hours.
Take out of water and wash and clean in clear water.
Let stand in ice water for 3 hours. Drain 30 minutes.
Put the pickling spice, dill seed and celery seed in cheesecloth bag.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over pickles and let stand 24 hours.
Put with this the bag of spices.
Put in kettle (I use my canner) and bring to a boil.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Put sprig of dill in jar before sealing.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook brown sugar and butter until glossy, approximately 3 minutes.
Set
aside.
Beat milk, yolks and flour and add to butter
mixture.
Cook on medium-high for 5 to 8 minutes. Pour in pie crust.

title: potato skins
directions: Prick potatoes with fork.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cut each potato lengthwise into quarters.
Scoop out the insides, leaving 1/2-inch thick shells.
(Reserve pulp for another use.) Arrange potato shells, skin side up, on a baking sheet.
Spray skins evenly with nonstick coating.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, cocoa and flour. Mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until
light and creamy.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and rind and pour into crust. Beat egg whites until
foamy,
then	gradually
add 1/4 cup of sugar; beat until stiff and
spread
on
top
of pie.
Bake in preheated oven until golden brown.

title: hobo chicken dinner
directions: Spray skillet with non-stick spray and brown chicken on both sides.
Place each breast on a piece of aluminum foil, and divide chopped vegetables between then.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle 1 tsp. tarragon over top of chicken and vegetables.
Bend up sides of foil and pour 2 Tbsp. wine on each portion.
Crimp foil at top to form a packet.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve entire package to each person.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients.
When done, add remaining ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: taco fantastaco
directions: Brown beef with chili powder; drain well.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, corn chips, olives, cheese and prepared dressing.
Serve in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Garnish with sour cream and avocado garnish.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix hamburg, corn, pepper, onion and tomato.
Just before serving add lettuce, chips and dressing.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend.
Chill until thickened.
Serve with chips.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and cook, then add pimentos.
Cook noodles as it says on package.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. ryeback's shipwreck
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
In deep casserole dish, layer 1/3 of the beef, 1/3 of sliced onions and potatoes and 1 can of kidney beans.
Do this twice more, until all meat, potatoes and onions are added.
Pour can of tomato sauce over top.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly, then add 1/2 cup milk to make a smooth paste.
Pour mixture slowly into remaining milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
Cover and cook over hot water until starch is thoroughly cooked, about 15 minutes.
Pour a small amount of the thickened sauce into yolks, then return yolk mixture to double boiler to cook, stirring until thickens, 2-3 minutes. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool mixture in refrigerator before filling cases.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin spice, salt, sugar and milk, blending well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 baking dish and sprinkle cake mix and nuts over top.
Drizzle melted butter over all; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour, testing for doneness by inserting a knife in center; if it comes out clean, it is done.

title: caramel dip
directions: Blend and serve with apple wedges.

title: chicken, wine, mushrooms
directions: Skin and trim fat from chicken.
Shake in bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in salad oil.
Reduce heat to low; add wine, mushrooms, tarragon, thyme and brown sugar.
Cover and simmer until fork-tender.
Serve with rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Put peaches on the bottom, draining off some of the liquid.
In separate bowl, mix flour, sugar and baking powder. Add egg and mix until it is in small clumps. Scatter over fruit. Drizzle with margarine. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yum-yum!

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Strain and discard spices.
Serve hot. Makes 2 3/4 quarts.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut well.
Add listed ingredients.
Mix well with a fork.
Store in airtight bowl or jar in the refrigerator.
Let stand 24 hours before using to let flavors blend.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat pineapple, add juice of one lemon and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and remove from heat.
Add gelatine which has been soaked in 1/2 cup cold water for one minute.
Add to pineapple mixture and let cool.
When it begins to congeal, add cheese and whipped cream.
Mix well.
Let congeal in refrigerator; 9-inch square pan makes good size container.
Cut into 16 serving pieces, or larger for the larger appetites.

title: 24-hour polish pickles
directions: Brine:
Combine water, vinegar, salt and sugar in pot.
Bring to slow boil.
Cool to room temperature.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine.
Place in freezer and stir several times during freezing.
Makes about 3-quarts.

title: quail southern style
directions: Clean quail.
Split down back or leave whole.
Dust with combined flour, salt and pepper.
Heat fat in skillet and brown quails.
Add cream, cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes or until tender.
Thicken gravy, if desired.

title: baked parsley chicken
directions: Pour dressing over chicken breasts; refrigerate for several hours.
Drain and save liquid.
Combine water and egg.
Combine cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in egg and then in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish and spoon reserved liquid over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot cheese and sausage dip(for added zip use hot italian sausage)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook sausage and green onions 4 minutes or until sausage is browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Heat until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Pour into heated serving dish or fondue pot.
Garnish with green onions.
Serve with celery sticks, carrot sticks, bagel chips or tortilla chips for dipping.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: mighty meatloaf
directions: Mix eggs, milk, seasonings, and crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add the diced onion, parsley.
Line the baking dish with onion slices and then lay bacon cross-wise across (to be bottom of loaf). Gently mix meat into mixture and fill pan.
Bake at 350 deg until meat thermometer reads 170 deg, about 90 minutes.
Serve with parsley infused mashed potatoes.
Serves many.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain liquid off beets into saucepan; put beets into jar.
To the liquid, add the sugar, vinegar and pickling spices.
Boil for about 3 minutes; pour over beets.
Seal.
The longer they pickle, the better.

title: admonition coconut cake
directions: The night before making cake combine sugar, sour cream and coconut and refrigerate.
Next day, make cake as directed on package.
When cake layers have cooled, slice in half to make 4 layers.
Fill and frost with sour cream mixture.
Don't cut for four days.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Boil all ingredients, except meat, to make sauce.
Pull meat apart and cut up.
Put in sauce and simmer.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Drain pineapple. Add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Bring liquid to a boil and add Jell-O to dissolve.
Add 1 cup cold water, blueberry filling and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Beat sour cream, sugar and cream cheese together and add to top of Jell-O. Chill until firm.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together shortening and peanut butter; gradually add sugar and brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well, blending in mix thoroughly.
Shape teaspoon rounded balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place unwrapped candy kiss in center of cookies. Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: fish chowder
directions: Peel and cube the potatoes.
Cook potatoes in a pan with just enough water to cover them.
Cook until tender.
Brown salt pork pieces in frypan.
Add to the potatoes.
Fry cut-up onion in fat from salt pork.
Add to the potatoes.
Put pieces of fish on top of the cooked potatoes.
Cook for about 3 to 4 minutes longer. Add the can of evaporated milk.
Stir and cook until just hot. Salt and pepper, if desired.
Serves 6 persons.

title: fly ups
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt, continue beating, then add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold in chocolate chips and drop on a cookie sheet lined with brown paper (ungreased).
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from paper 2 minutes after they have been taken from the oven.

title: baked vidalias
directions: Core onion.
Fill hollow with salt, pepper, bouillon and butter.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes (if large) or until desired tenderness.

title: great american brownie
directions: Melt the butter, semi-sweet chocolate and unsweetened chocolate in a large heavy saucepan over low heat. Remove from the heat. Add the sugar, eggs, flour, salt and vanilla in the order listed, beating well after each addition.
Pour into a greased foil-lined 8 x 8 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until the brownies just begin to pull from the sides of the dish. Cool in the dish on a wire rack to room temperature.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to pkg. directions and let cool. Mix tomatoes, bell pepper, green onion, onion, pickles and bacon. In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise and pickle juice together. Crumble corn bread into a shallow dish; add a layer of tomato mixture; nest, spread a layer of mayonnaise mixture; repeat layers until complete. Top with additional crumbled bacon and green onions if desired. Serve as a cool dish.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in low oven at 275° for 10 minutes and cool.
Mix Philadelphia cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar. Pour on graham crust.
Top with cherries mixed with Cool Whip. Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Add corn with its liquid, stewed tomatoes, chili beef soup, tomato soup, chopped olives and taco seasoning.
Simmer together for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Form ball. Serve with crackers.

title: yellow rice and chicken
directions: Place rice in bottom of well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
(Regular white rice may be used, but yellow rice is attractive.)
Cut chicken breasts in halves.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice, preferably in one layer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend the three kinds of soup together with milk.
Pour over chicken; top with potato chips and then pour butter over all. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 2 hours or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer ingredients.
Dot with butter and bake, uncovered, 1 1/4 hours. Serves 4.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow pan.
Top each piece with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Thin soup with 1/2 can water and pour over chicken.
Combine stuffing and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: anna's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, milk, garlic, salt and pepper. Form into 40 meatballs, using a rounded teaspoonful for each one.
Brown meatballs lightly in oil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Combine chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over meatballs and heat, stirring until jelly is melted. Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce thickens.
